00:12:53.512 --> 00:12:55.577
(IN SINGSONG)
Winner winner,
charcoal dinner...

00:12:55.713 --> 00:12:56.975
(GASPS)

00:12:57.110 --> 00:12:59.314
(SNORING SOFTLY)

00:13:00.747 --> 00:13:03.582
(TRANQUIL MUSIC PLAYING)
(BELL JINGLES SOFTLY)

00:13:17.096 --> 00:13:19.103
(COUGHING)

00:13:20.775 --> 00:13:22.666
Head to bed,
I'll close things up.

00:13:22.801 --> 00:13:25.738
Still have much
to prepare for Red Dot Sale.

00:13:25.873 --> 00:13:28.446
Dad, I'll take
care of it.
You need to rest.

00:13:28.581 --> 00:13:29.641
(TIMER RINGING)

00:13:30.783 --> 00:13:32.146
(DINGS)
How?

00:13:32.281 --> 00:13:33.484
I learned
from the best.

00:13:33.619 --> 00:13:34.616
(BOTH LAUGH)

00:13:34.752 --> 00:13:36.279
(COUGHS)

00:13:36.414 --> 00:13:38.017
(SIGHS) I am old.

00:13:38.153 --> 00:13:39.990
I can't do this forever.

00:13:40.126 --> 00:13:42.027
Now that you've
beaten my time,

00:13:42.162 --> 00:13:44.221
there's only one thing
you haven't done.

00:13:44.357 --> 00:13:46.163
Tomorrow I sleep in

00:13:46.299 --> 00:13:49.535
and I want you to run shop
for Red Dot Sale.

00:13:49.670 --> 00:13:51.466
Seriously? By myself?

00:13:51.601 --> 00:13:54.336
If you can do that
without losing your temper,

00:13:54.471 --> 00:13:56.910
it will show me
you are able to take over.

00:13:57.777 --> 00:13:58.912
You got it, Ashfa.

00:14:02.478 --> 00:14:04.778
I won't let you down, I swear.
You'll see.

00:14:04.914 --> 00:14:05.919
BERNIE: Mm.

00:14:06.653 --> 00:14:07.745
Good daughter.

00:14:11.384 --> 00:14:14.057
Yes! (SQUEALS, GIGGLES)

00:14:14.193 --> 00:14:17.557
Blue Flame, please,
let this go my way.

00:14:24.631 --> 00:14:27.532
(VEHICLE PUTTERING)
(HORN HONKS)

00:14:27.668 --> 00:14:29.041
WOMAN: Good morning!
MAN: Morning!

00:14:34.748 --> 00:14:35.877
EMBER: Take a breath.

00:14:36.012 --> 00:14:37.247
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

00:14:39.851 --> 00:14:41.086
Calm as a candle.

00:14:41.755 --> 00:14:44.417
(PATRONS CLAMORING)

00:14:44.553 --> 00:14:46.960
Morning, welcome
to The Fireplace.

00:14:49.694 --> 00:14:51.059
Whew!

00:14:51.195 --> 00:14:52.763
(GRUNTING)
Whoa, whoa.

00:14:52.898 --> 00:14:53.864
They're all the same.

00:14:53.999 --> 00:14:54.932
Just take one from the top.

00:14:55.068 --> 00:14:56.329
(GRUNTS)
Thanks for shopping.

00:14:56.464 --> 00:14:58.763
(GRUNTS) So many
stickers for sale.

00:15:00.039 --> 00:15:01.369
Are these fragile?
No, wait.

00:15:01.504 --> 00:15:03.072
(OBJECTS CLATTER, SMASH)
(STIFLED SCREAM)

00:15:03.207 --> 00:15:04.175
You have to pay
before you eat.

00:15:06.279 --> 00:15:07.747
MAN 1: Uh, what's
your return policy?

00:15:07.882 --> 00:15:09.442
MAN 2: Does this come
in a large?

00:15:09.577 --> 00:15:10.911
(HUFFING)
(PATRONS CLAMORING)

00:15:11.046 --> 00:15:11.979
Take breath.

00:15:12.114 --> 00:15:13.078
My dad broke this.

00:15:13.213 --> 00:15:14.384
Make connection.

00:15:14.519 --> 00:15:15.950
Mind if I test this kettle?
(KETTLE WHISTLING)

00:15:16.085 --> 00:15:17.456
(HUFFING RAPIDLY)

00:15:17.591 --> 00:15:18.789
(MUFFLED GRUNT)

00:15:18.925 --> 00:15:20.152
Be back
in five minutes.

00:15:20.287 --> 00:15:21.758
(MUFFLED GRUNTING)

00:15:21.893 --> 00:15:23.887
(GASPING RAPIDLY)

00:15:25.258 --> 00:15:28.192
(SCREAMS)

00:15:28.327 --> 00:15:29.970
(PANTING)

00:15:31.000 --> 00:15:33.501
(RATTLING)

00:15:35.909 --> 00:15:37.276
(RATTLING CONTINUES)
Huh?

00:15:37.412 --> 00:15:38.374
Huh?

00:15:39.878 --> 00:15:41.806
(GASPS, GRUNTING)

00:15:41.941 --> 00:15:44.713
(UPTEMPO INDIAN CLASSICAL
MUSIC PLAYING)

00:15:44.849 --> 00:15:45.843
(GASPS)

00:15:51.691 --> 00:15:53.316
(GRUNTING)

00:15:53.451 --> 00:15:54.995
(STRAINING)

00:15:55.893 --> 00:15:58.391
(PANTING)

00:15:58.526 --> 00:15:59.956
Oh, no, no,
no, no, no.

00:16:01.133 --> 00:16:03.597
Stupid temper.
Not today.

00:16:04.902 --> 00:16:06.497
(GRUNTS, GULPS)

00:16:06.633 --> 00:16:08.132
What is wrong
with me?

00:16:08.267 --> 00:16:09.570
(BUBBLING)

00:16:10.570 --> 00:16:12.270
(MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

00:16:12.406 --> 00:16:14.575
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

00:16:17.442 --> 00:16:19.448
(SOBBING)

00:16:20.588 --> 00:16:21.681
What the...?

00:16:23.350 --> 00:16:25.155
What a happy family.

00:16:25.291 --> 00:16:27.516
(SNIFFLES)
Is that you
and your dad?

00:16:27.652 --> 00:16:29.896
I love dads. (GASPS)

00:16:30.031 --> 00:16:33.627
And it's your birthday.
(SOBS)

00:16:33.763 --> 00:16:35.633
Who are you?
What are you
doing here?

00:16:35.769 --> 00:16:37.028
I don't know.

00:16:37.163 --> 00:16:38.564
I was searching
for a leak
on the other side

00:16:38.699 --> 00:16:40.699
of the river
and got sucked in.

00:16:40.835 --> 00:16:43.503
This is bad,
I can't lose another job.

00:16:43.639 --> 00:16:46.369
I just can't seem
to find my flow.

00:16:46.504 --> 00:16:47.911
(BUBBLING)

00:16:48.046 --> 00:16:49.115
Dang!
(GROANS)

00:16:49.250 --> 00:16:51.241
That pipe squished me
all out of shape.

00:16:51.376 --> 00:16:52.551
(GURGLES)

00:16:52.687 --> 00:16:53.611
That's better.

00:16:53.746 --> 00:16:55.146
Dude, just get
out of here.

00:16:55.282 --> 00:16:57.420
I gotta clean this
mess before my dad
sees what I did.

00:16:58.185 --> 00:16:59.191
Ooh...

00:16:59.660 --> 00:17:00.687
Actually...

00:17:05.464 --> 00:17:07.161
I'm afraid I'm gonna
have to write you a ticket.

00:17:07.297 --> 00:17:08.558
A ticket?
Yeah.

00:17:08.693 --> 00:17:10.102
I'm a city inspector,

00:17:10.237 --> 00:17:12.138
and this pipe is definitely
not up to code.

00:17:12.273 --> 00:17:15.237
I sucked a city inspector
into our pipes?

00:17:15.372 --> 00:17:17.171
I know. Ironic, right?
(CLANKING)

00:17:17.307 --> 00:17:18.372
Stop messing with that.

00:17:18.508 --> 00:17:19.777
Well, I need
to make sure it's solid.

00:17:19.913 --> 00:17:20.876
Everything's solid.

00:17:21.012 --> 00:17:21.981
I should know.

00:17:22.117 --> 00:17:24.243
My dad rebuilt
this place himself.

00:17:24.379 --> 00:17:26.614
Wait, your dad did?

00:17:26.749 --> 00:17:30.055
Yes, with his bare hands,
every brick and board.

00:17:30.191 --> 00:17:31.858
It was a ruin
when he found it.

00:17:31.993 --> 00:17:35.122
Wow. He did all
of this himself?

00:17:35.257 --> 00:17:36.353
Without permits?

00:17:36.489 --> 00:17:37.855
Uh... (GULPS)

00:17:37.990 --> 00:17:39.722
I'm gonna have
to write that up too.

00:17:39.858 --> 00:17:41.296
First, I'm sucked
into a pipe

00:17:41.431 --> 00:17:42.662
and now I have
to write citations

00:17:42.797 --> 00:17:44.432
that could get this place
shut down.

00:17:44.567 --> 00:17:46.671
Oh, gosh.
It's just too much.

00:17:46.807 --> 00:17:48.564
Shut us down?

00:17:48.700 --> 00:17:50.536
I know, it's awful.

00:17:50.672 --> 00:17:52.305
No, you can't
shut us down, please.

00:17:52.440 --> 00:17:53.536
This is a big day for me.

00:17:53.671 --> 00:17:54.944
It's our Red Dot Sale.

00:17:55.079 --> 00:17:56.576
Hey, take it easy.

00:17:56.711 --> 00:17:58.180
This is as hard on me
as it is on you.

00:17:58.315 --> 00:17:59.612
Get back here.
Sorry.

00:17:59.747 --> 00:18:00.918
I got to get these
to City Hall

00:18:01.054 --> 00:18:02.654
before the end
of my shift.

00:18:02.789 --> 00:18:04.883
(GRUNTS, GROANS)

00:18:06.253 --> 00:18:07.222
Flame.

00:18:07.358 --> 00:18:09.492
(UPTEMPO FUSION
MUSIC PLAYING)

00:18:11.392 --> 00:18:12.528
Get back here.

00:18:13.391 --> 00:18:14.326
Hmm?

00:18:14.461 --> 00:18:16.532
(GROANS, PANTING)

00:18:19.234 --> 00:18:20.403
WOMAN: Huh?

00:18:20.539 --> 00:18:22.406
ANNOUNCER: Next stop,
Element City.

00:18:25.037 --> 00:18:26.946
(SIGHS)
(SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE)

00:18:27.081 --> 00:18:29.011
(TRAIN HORN BLOWS)
(GROANS)

00:18:29.147 --> 00:18:31.041
(HUFFS RAPIDLY, GROANS)

00:18:31.443 --> 00:18:32.379
(GRUNTS)

00:18:32.515 --> 00:18:34.847
(UPBEAT FUSION MUSIC PLAYING)

00:18:38.825 --> 00:18:40.292
(PANTING)

00:18:40.892 --> 00:18:41.925
(GASPS)

00:18:42.061 --> 00:18:44.622
(PASSENGERS CHATTERING)

00:18:44.758 --> 00:18:45.962
(TRAIN RATTLES)
(GRUNTS) Whoa!

00:18:46.097 --> 00:18:47.026
(GASPS)
Hey!

00:18:47.162 --> 00:18:48.201
Sorry.

00:18:53.405 --> 00:18:55.769
(UPBEAT FUSION MUSIC
CONTINUES)

00:18:59.010 --> 00:19:00.004
(GASPS)

00:19:01.979 --> 00:19:03.707
(GRUNTS)

00:19:03.842 --> 00:19:05.680
(EXCLAIMS, BREATHES HEAVILY)

00:19:06.788 --> 00:19:08.518
Hey! (SHUDDERS)

00:19:10.657 --> 00:19:11.851
Huh?

00:19:14.162 --> 00:19:16.020
What the...?
(TRAIN HORN BLOWS)

00:19:21.159 --> 00:19:22.525
ANNOUNCER:
This stop, City Hall.

00:19:22.660 --> 00:19:23.834
Uh... (GASPING)

00:19:23.969 --> 00:19:25.128
Hands off!

00:19:25.930 --> 00:19:27.331
(GROANS) Ooh.
MAN: Hey!

00:19:27.466 --> 00:19:28.571
Sorry.

00:19:30.372 --> 00:19:31.706
(ENGINES WHIRRING)

00:19:33.307 --> 00:19:34.412
Ugh.

00:19:35.573 --> 00:19:36.810
Stop!

00:19:37.510 --> 00:19:39.175
(GRUNTING)

00:19:39.786 --> 00:19:41.146
Hey!

00:19:41.282 --> 00:19:42.216
Hey!

00:19:42.351 --> 00:19:44.323
(SHOUTS, GRUNTS)

00:19:45.488 --> 00:19:47.192
Stop.
(HORN BLARES)

00:19:47.328 --> 00:19:49.427
(GROANS) My new jacket.
(GROANS)

00:19:50.228 --> 00:19:51.891
Whoa!
(GRUNTING)

00:19:55.164 --> 00:19:56.197
(GRUNTS)

00:19:56.332 --> 00:19:57.567
(CHILDREN EXCLAIM)

00:20:01.236 --> 00:20:02.205
(GRUNTS)

00:20:02.341 --> 00:20:04.101
(GROANS)
(PEOPLE GASP)

00:20:05.208 --> 00:20:06.202
(SHOUTS)

00:20:08.573 --> 00:20:09.579
(GASPS)

00:20:10.844 --> 00:20:12.610
(EMBER GASPS)
(PANTING)

00:20:12.746 --> 00:20:15.019
(HUFFS RAPIDLY,
GRUNTING)

00:20:15.154 --> 00:20:17.114
(BOTH PANTING RAPIDLY)

00:20:21.454 --> 00:20:22.895
(GRUNTS)

00:20:23.030 --> 00:20:24.394
(GROANS)
(HORN BLARES)

00:20:24.530 --> 00:20:26.266
(TIRES SCREECH)
MAN IN TRUCK: Hey!

00:20:30.333 --> 00:20:32.071
Huh? My chili oil!

00:20:32.206 --> 00:20:33.970
(YELPS)
(EMBER PANTING)

00:20:34.105 --> 00:20:35.437
Come on, guy.

00:20:35.573 --> 00:20:37.737
You can't get
through this.

00:20:37.873 --> 00:20:40.472
So, it is time
to hand them over.

00:20:40.607 --> 00:20:42.039
Oh, boy,
I'm sorry.

00:20:42.175 --> 00:20:44.412
This is gonna be
really disappointing for you.

00:20:44.547 --> 00:20:46.314
Oh, no, no, no,
no, no, no.

00:20:46.450 --> 00:20:47.619
No, no, no,
no, no, no.

00:20:47.755 --> 00:20:49.183
Sorry.

00:20:49.318 --> 00:20:50.348
Please...

00:20:50.484 --> 00:20:51.984
No. (GROANS)

00:20:53.126 --> 00:20:54.954
You don't understand.

00:20:57.930 --> 00:20:59.164
Whoa.

00:20:59.299 --> 00:21:02.433
EMBER: This shop
is my dad's dream.

00:21:02.568 --> 00:21:04.760
If I'm the reason
it gets shut down,

00:21:04.895 --> 00:21:05.965
it will kill him.

00:21:06.301 --> 00:21:07.306
Oh.

00:21:07.441 --> 00:21:09.672
He will never trust me
to take over.

00:21:10.805 --> 00:21:12.910
Why didn't you
say that before?

00:21:13.045 --> 00:21:14.314
(CLEARS THROAT)

00:21:14.449 --> 00:21:16.239
Wait, does that mean
you'll tear up the tickets?

00:21:16.374 --> 00:21:19.017
I mean, I would,
but I just sent them over

00:21:19.153 --> 00:21:20.117
to the processing department.

00:21:20.252 --> 00:21:21.521
(GROANS FRUSTRATEDLY)

00:21:21.656 --> 00:21:23.180
But I can take you there
so you can plead your case.

00:21:24.783 --> 00:21:26.282
(TUBES WHOOSHING)

00:21:30.556 --> 00:21:31.529
(GRUNTS)

00:21:33.062 --> 00:21:35.335
(MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING)
(ANIMALS TRILLING)

00:21:42.568 --> 00:21:43.541
Whoa!

00:21:46.237 --> 00:21:48.671
CITY INSPECTOR:
Hey, Fern. (CHUCKLES)

00:21:48.807 --> 00:21:49.982
How you doing?

00:21:50.118 --> 00:21:51.817
(DULLY) Living the dream.

00:21:51.952 --> 00:21:53.245
(CHUCKLES)

00:21:53.381 --> 00:21:55.980
You know those citations
I just gave you from Firetown?

00:21:56.116 --> 00:21:59.356
I was about to send them
to Mrs. Cumulus.

00:21:59.491 --> 00:22:01.959
Then get sprayed
for fungus rot.

00:22:02.094 --> 00:22:03.319
BOTH: Wait.

00:22:04.727 --> 00:22:05.892
Tell him
what you told me

00:22:06.027 --> 00:22:07.394
about your dad
and letting him down.

00:22:07.530 --> 00:22:08.593
No. That's personal.

00:22:08.728 --> 00:22:09.727
It really got to me.

00:22:09.862 --> 00:22:11.335
He might feel it too.

00:22:11.471 --> 00:22:12.796
Her dad will be sup...
Nope.

00:22:12.932 --> 00:22:13.864
...sup...
Nope.

00:22:14.000 --> 00:22:16.307
...super disappointed in her.

00:22:16.443 --> 00:22:18.168
Stop it.
He might even be...

00:22:18.304 --> 00:22:20.947
(GROANS) ashamed.
What are you doing?

00:22:21.082 --> 00:22:22.273
But the main thing is,

00:22:22.408 --> 00:22:24.083
if her father can't retire...
(HUFFING RAPIDLY)

00:22:24.219 --> 00:22:26.346
...it will be all Ember's f...

00:22:26.482 --> 00:22:27.750
Stop talking!

00:22:35.193 --> 00:22:36.429
(WATER BUBBLES)

00:22:37.064 --> 00:22:38.024
(DESK CREAKS)

00:22:40.194 --> 00:22:42.901
Looks like I'm going home
early today.

00:22:43.036 --> 00:22:44.001
No, don't.

00:22:44.136 --> 00:22:45.503
(TUBE WARBLES)

00:22:45.639 --> 00:22:48.699
Expect to get shut down
within a week.

00:22:48.834 --> 00:22:49.838
Have a good one.

00:22:51.880 --> 00:22:53.075
(GROANS)

00:22:53.210 --> 00:22:54.205
Sorry.

00:22:57.544 --> 00:22:58.550
(SIGHS)

00:23:00.384 --> 00:23:02.187
(GASPS) What?

00:23:02.323 --> 00:23:04.116
(BELL JINGLES)
Already?

00:23:04.859 --> 00:23:05.784
Hello?

00:23:05.919 --> 00:23:07.922
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

00:23:08.857 --> 00:23:10.826
(BERNIE COUGHING)
(GASPS)

00:23:13.057 --> 00:23:14.390
(CONTINUES COUGHING)

00:23:17.195 --> 00:23:19.567
Oh, no. Dad,
what happened?

00:23:19.702 --> 00:23:21.273
We lucky
nobody hurt.

00:23:21.408 --> 00:23:22.932
It ruined
Red Dot Sale.

00:23:23.068 --> 00:23:24.739
Did he do this?
Who?

00:23:24.874 --> 00:23:26.471
The Water guy
I see you chase.

00:23:26.607 --> 00:23:27.573
(GROANS)

00:23:27.708 --> 00:23:29.311
Oh, uh... Um...

00:23:29.447 --> 00:23:31.779
Yeah, he did. Uh...

00:23:31.914 --> 00:23:32.978
He just broke
through a pipe.

00:23:33.114 --> 00:23:34.585
(CLEARS THROAT)
I don't know why.

00:23:34.720 --> 00:23:36.487
Luckily, I was able
to close it off.

00:23:36.623 --> 00:23:38.281
I, uh, couldn't
catch him though.

00:23:38.417 --> 00:23:40.955
Water, always trying
to water us down.

00:23:41.090 --> 00:23:44.022
He was a Water person,
Dad, not just water.

00:23:44.158 --> 00:23:46.595
Ah, same thing.
And why is water in pipes?

00:23:46.730 --> 00:23:48.465
City shut down
years ago.

00:23:48.600 --> 00:23:50.595
There should be
no water.

00:23:50.730 --> 00:23:52.263
(COUGHS)
Dad!

00:23:54.139 --> 00:23:55.470
Bernie.

00:23:55.605 --> 00:23:56.767
We will get through this.

00:23:56.902 --> 00:23:58.170
Just like before.

00:23:58.506 --> 00:23:59.874
Before?

00:24:00.009 --> 00:24:02.745
There is a reason
we left Fire Land.

00:24:02.880 --> 00:24:06.912
Oh, Ember,
we loved it there so much.

00:24:07.047 --> 00:24:09.487
Most everyone
had a Blue Flame.

00:24:09.623 --> 00:24:12.182
And it connected us
all together.

00:24:12.317 --> 00:24:15.127
To our traditions.
Our family.

00:24:15.263 --> 00:24:17.124
It was hard living.

00:24:17.259 --> 00:24:20.159
But your father began
to build a life for us.

00:24:20.294 --> 00:24:22.334
We put everything into it.
(WIND HOWLING)

00:24:22.469 --> 00:24:24.460
But then a great storm came.

00:24:31.474 --> 00:24:32.545
(CRASHING)

00:24:35.178 --> 00:24:38.708
(SOLEMN MUSIC PLAYING)
All was lost for us.

00:24:38.843 --> 00:24:43.879
Your father understood
we had to leave everything.

00:24:44.015 --> 00:24:45.285
Our home.

00:24:45.420 --> 00:24:48.253
It was the only way
to create a better life.

00:24:57.063 --> 00:24:58.703
It was the last time

00:24:58.838 --> 00:25:00.903
your father ever
saw his family.

00:25:03.202 --> 00:25:05.341
That is why
we came here.

00:25:05.476 --> 00:25:07.547
To build all this.

00:25:13.985 --> 00:25:16.422
Ashfa,
nothing will happen
to this shop

00:25:16.557 --> 00:25:18.888
or the flame again,
I promise.

00:25:20.117 --> 00:25:22.518
Mm. Good daughter.

00:25:29.032 --> 00:25:31.197
(HIP-HOP SONG PLAYING
ON HEADPHONES)

00:25:33.274 --> 00:25:35.063
(FIRE ROARS SOFTLY)

00:25:35.199 --> 00:25:36.736
(YELPS) Fire! Fire!

00:25:36.872 --> 00:25:38.406
Ah! Fire!
Hey, hey!

00:25:38.541 --> 00:25:39.937
Oh, sorry.

00:25:40.072 --> 00:25:42.014
You're so hot. (BLOWS)

00:25:42.149 --> 00:25:43.110
Excuse me?

00:25:44.212 --> 00:25:46.243
No, I mean, like,
you're smoking.

00:25:46.378 --> 00:25:47.551
No, I didn't
mean it like that.

00:25:47.686 --> 00:25:49.411
Are you done yet?
Yes, please.

00:25:49.547 --> 00:25:51.018
I'm waiting to talk
to your boss.

00:25:51.154 --> 00:25:54.119
So, make like a stream
and flow somewhere else.

00:25:54.255 --> 00:25:55.955
Actually, Gale
won't be in today.

00:25:56.090 --> 00:25:57.894
She's a huge
airball fan

00:25:58.030 --> 00:26:00.397
and the Windbreakers
are finally
in the playoffs.

00:26:00.533 --> 00:26:02.566
Toot toot.
(GROANS)

00:26:02.701 --> 00:26:04.599
Okay. Well,
I just came by

00:26:04.735 --> 00:26:05.898
because I left
my passes

00:26:06.033 --> 00:26:07.570
for the game
here last night.

00:26:07.706 --> 00:26:09.906
Passes?
Like, plural?

00:26:11.235 --> 00:26:12.370
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

00:26:13.773 --> 00:26:14.739
(GASPS)

00:26:14.874 --> 00:26:17.148
(FANS CHANTING)

00:26:17.283 --> 00:26:19.982
(KERNKRAFT 400 (SPORT CHANT
STADIUM REMIX) PLAYING)

00:26:26.721 --> 00:26:27.726
(PLAYER GRUNTS)

00:26:29.393 --> 00:26:31.356
(GRUNTING)

00:26:38.734 --> 00:26:40.266
(SPECTATORS GROAN)

00:26:41.032 --> 00:26:41.966
Where is she?

00:26:42.102 --> 00:26:43.475
Up there,
in that skybox.

00:26:43.610 --> 00:26:45.603
Come on!
(LIGHTNING CRACKLES)

00:26:45.739 --> 00:26:46.710
Oh.

00:26:46.846 --> 00:26:49.605
Okay. Time to cancel
some tickets.

00:26:50.781 --> 00:26:52.647
VENDOR:
Toot Toot juice.

00:26:52.783 --> 00:26:54.819
Get your
Toot Toot juice.

00:26:55.585 --> 00:26:56.787
Toot Toot juice,

00:26:56.922 --> 00:26:59.023
get your
Toot Toot juice.
(CHATTER STOPS)

00:26:59.159 --> 00:27:00.457
(SLURPS)

00:27:00.593 --> 00:27:02.121
You'll be great.
This way.

00:27:02.257 --> 00:27:03.626
EMBER: Excuse me.
Jimmy, what's up?

00:27:03.761 --> 00:27:05.554
Sorry. Pardon.
Wendy.

00:27:05.689 --> 00:27:07.895
Oh. Sorry.
Fire girl coming through.

00:27:08.031 --> 00:27:10.865
Break some wind!
(LIGHTNING CRACKLES)

00:27:11.000 --> 00:27:12.363
Hi, Gale,
how you doing?

00:27:12.498 --> 00:27:14.267
Look at the score,
what do you think?

00:27:14.402 --> 00:27:17.202
Blow the ball, not the game!
(LIGHTNING CRACKLES)

00:27:17.337 --> 00:27:21.169
(HUFFS) Yeah, so, uh, Gale.
(CHUCKLES)

00:27:21.305 --> 00:27:22.813
My name is Ember Lumen.

00:27:22.948 --> 00:27:24.848
My family runs a Fire shop.
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

00:27:24.984 --> 00:27:26.819
Wade wrote us a bunch
of tickets yesterday...

00:27:26.954 --> 00:27:28.547
What kind of call was that?
(SPECTATORS GROAN)

00:27:28.683 --> 00:27:32.017
Oh, Lumen?
Yeah, a Fire shop
with 30 citations.

00:27:32.152 --> 00:27:33.589
Thirty?
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

00:27:33.725 --> 00:27:36.223
Anyway, friend, I was hoping

00:27:36.358 --> 00:27:37.723
we could work something out.
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

00:27:37.859 --> 00:27:38.929
Come on, ref!

00:27:39.064 --> 00:27:40.996
Are your eyes
in the back of your head?

00:27:41.131 --> 00:27:43.566
(SPECTATORS BOOING)
(GRUNTS, GROWLS)

00:27:43.701 --> 00:27:45.467
Oh, no.
Yeah, bummer.

00:27:45.602 --> 00:27:46.536
Oh, yeah.

00:27:46.672 --> 00:27:49.031
Okay, so, the 30 citations.

00:27:49.166 --> 00:27:50.366
Do you mind?

00:27:50.501 --> 00:27:52.877
There's a game going on.
Fireball.

00:27:53.378 --> 00:27:54.406
Fireball?

00:27:55.449 --> 00:27:56.845
Actually,
I do mind.

00:27:56.981 --> 00:27:58.878
This is my life
we're talking about.

00:27:59.014 --> 00:28:00.080
Not just
some game.

00:28:00.216 --> 00:28:02.888
Some game?
This is the playoffs.

00:28:03.024 --> 00:28:05.724
So, forgive me if I don't want
to hear a sob story

00:28:05.860 --> 00:28:08.386
about the problems
of some little shop.

00:28:08.522 --> 00:28:11.554
Well, that little shop
matters way more

00:28:11.689 --> 00:28:13.431
than a bunch
of overpaid cloud puffs

00:28:13.567 --> 00:28:14.826
blowing some ball around.

00:28:14.961 --> 00:28:16.393
I dare you,

00:28:16.529 --> 00:28:19.937
say "cloud puffs"
one more time.

00:28:20.670 --> 00:28:22.867
Cloud puffs.

00:28:23.002 --> 00:28:24.643
(BOTH GROWL)

00:28:24.779 --> 00:28:25.978
WADE: Oh, no!
(SPECTATORS BOOING)

00:28:26.114 --> 00:28:27.109
Lutz!

00:28:28.646 --> 00:28:30.046
(BLOWS, GRUNTS)

00:28:31.341 --> 00:28:32.909
(SPECTATORS GROAN)

00:28:33.045 --> 00:28:34.153
(GASPS)

00:28:34.288 --> 00:28:35.881
(CHIMING)

00:28:36.017 --> 00:28:37.915
(SPECTATORS BOOING)

00:28:38.050 --> 00:28:38.986
Lutz, man.

00:28:39.121 --> 00:28:40.152
He's been
in such a funk

00:28:40.288 --> 00:28:41.717
'cause his mom
has been sick.

00:28:43.758 --> 00:28:45.191
(BOOING)

00:28:45.327 --> 00:28:49.194
That is so not cool,
he's doing his best.

00:28:49.329 --> 00:28:51.969
(LOUDLY)
We love you, Lutz!

00:28:52.703 --> 00:28:54.840
(VOICE CRACKING) Lutz!

00:28:55.475 --> 00:28:58.302
We love you, Lutz!

00:28:58.437 --> 00:29:01.206
We love you, Lutz!
Come on!

00:29:01.342 --> 00:29:04.078
We love you, Lutz!
Everybody!

00:29:04.214 --> 00:29:08.116
ALL: We love you, Lutz!
We love you, Lutz!

00:29:08.251 --> 00:29:11.282
We love you, Lutz!
We love you, Lutz!

00:29:11.418 --> 00:29:15.394
Whoa!
(SPECTATORS CHEERING)

00:29:15.529 --> 00:29:17.324
(HOPEFUL MUSIC PLAYS)

00:29:24.230 --> 00:29:26.201
(PANTING, GRUNTING)

00:29:27.399 --> 00:29:28.834
(SPECTATORS CHEERING) Yeah!

00:29:28.969 --> 00:29:31.107
(KERNKRAFT 400 (SPORT CHANT
STADIUM REMIX) PLAYING)

00:29:33.879 --> 00:29:34.844
(WHISTLE BLOWS)
(CHEERING)

00:29:34.979 --> 00:29:36.647
Yay!
Yeah! Way to go, Lutz!

00:29:36.783 --> 00:29:38.879
(BLOWS)
WADE: Yeah, Lutz!

00:29:39.015 --> 00:29:40.548
That was amazing, Lutz!

00:29:40.683 --> 00:29:41.981
(CHUCKLES)

00:29:42.117 --> 00:29:44.853
(GRUNTS)
Yeah! Yeah! Yes!

00:29:44.988 --> 00:29:47.189
(CHUCKLES)
Whoo-hoo!

00:29:48.790 --> 00:29:49.785
Oh.

00:29:54.658 --> 00:29:57.560
Whoo-hoo!
What a comeback.

00:29:57.696 --> 00:30:00.330
Check out who found
the gift shop.

00:30:00.465 --> 00:30:01.968
Whoo!
I gotta admit,

00:30:02.103 --> 00:30:03.335
that was pretty cool.

00:30:03.471 --> 00:30:05.871
You can see why
I can get all churned up,

00:30:06.006 --> 00:30:09.473
but as a cloud puff
who used to come here
with her dad,

00:30:09.608 --> 00:30:11.845
all these wins mean
a little bit more.

00:30:11.980 --> 00:30:13.249
And as a fireball

00:30:13.385 --> 00:30:15.687
who's supposed
to take over
her dad's shop,

00:30:15.822 --> 00:30:17.479
I sure don't want
to let him down,

00:30:17.614 --> 00:30:19.056
and I could use a win, too.

00:30:20.624 --> 00:30:22.693
Now, I just got
to stop water
from coming in.

00:30:22.829 --> 00:30:25.258
Water? In Firetown?
Yeah.

00:30:25.393 --> 00:30:27.091
Water was shut off
to there years ago.

00:30:27.227 --> 00:30:28.329
Oh, forget the tickets,

00:30:28.464 --> 00:30:30.835
I'm gonna have
to take apart
your dad's shop

00:30:30.970 --> 00:30:32.403
to figure out
what's going on.

00:30:32.538 --> 00:30:33.631
You can't!

00:30:33.766 --> 00:30:36.499
My dad put his whole life
into that place.

00:30:36.634 --> 00:30:37.640
(GRUNTS) I bet
this is connected

00:30:37.775 --> 00:30:39.236
to that fluffing leak.

00:30:39.372 --> 00:30:40.371
Yeah, we've been trying

00:30:40.506 --> 00:30:41.945
to track down a leak
in the city.

00:30:42.081 --> 00:30:43.610
It's why I was
in the canal and...

00:30:43.746 --> 00:30:47.016
Wait, I know
where I got sucked
into Ember's shop.

00:30:47.152 --> 00:30:48.988
Ember and I could track
the water

00:30:49.123 --> 00:30:51.356
from her shop to find
the source of the leak.

00:30:51.492 --> 00:30:52.751
Keep talking.

00:30:52.886 --> 00:30:55.258
I could call in a city crew
to fix whatever we find.

00:30:55.393 --> 00:30:59.063
Yes. And there'd be
no need to touch
my dad's shop.

00:31:01.331 --> 00:31:02.731
You're lucky
you're a cute couple.

00:31:02.866 --> 00:31:04.063
Oh, we're not a...

00:31:04.198 --> 00:31:05.162
You got until Friday.

00:31:05.298 --> 00:31:06.397
If you can find the leak

00:31:06.532 --> 00:31:08.399
and get a crew
to fix it by then,

00:31:08.535 --> 00:31:09.731
those tickets
are forgiven.

00:31:09.867 --> 00:31:13.143
If not, your dad's shop
gets shut down.

00:31:13.744 --> 00:31:14.777
Whoo-hoo!

00:31:14.913 --> 00:31:17.249
Break wind!
Break wind!

00:31:17.384 --> 00:31:19.179
Thank you.

00:31:19.315 --> 00:31:21.349
(SIGHS IN RELIEF,
CHUCKLES)

00:31:21.484 --> 00:31:23.615
Please take all that off.
But I got you a hat.

00:31:24.523 --> 00:31:25.518
(BOOM)

00:31:27.460 --> 00:31:28.554
Okay.

00:31:29.953 --> 00:31:32.059
EMBER: Just keep out of sight,
okay?

00:31:32.195 --> 00:31:33.423
It'd be
a whole thing.

00:31:33.558 --> 00:31:35.132
BERNIE: Now water upstairs?

00:31:35.767 --> 00:31:37.436
It's in the walls.

00:31:37.571 --> 00:31:38.629
I don't understand.

00:31:38.764 --> 00:31:41.131
I fix one pipe
and another one leaks.

00:31:41.266 --> 00:31:42.407
(GROANS) Water!

00:31:42.542 --> 00:31:44.240
(COUGHING)

00:31:45.811 --> 00:31:46.941
How could
it be worse?

00:31:47.077 --> 00:31:48.278
Now that the water's back,

00:31:48.413 --> 00:31:50.914
the pressure is forcing it up
to all your pipes.

00:31:51.049 --> 00:31:53.080
We gotta find
the source.

00:31:53.215 --> 00:31:55.447
How did you even
end up here?

00:31:55.583 --> 00:31:57.285
WADE: Well,
I was in the canals

00:31:57.420 --> 00:31:59.085
checking the doors
for leaks,

00:31:59.221 --> 00:32:00.420
when I found some water

00:32:00.556 --> 00:32:02.124
that shouldn't
have been there.

00:32:02.260 --> 00:32:06.129
Rusty with a hint
of motor oil?

00:32:06.265 --> 00:32:07.795
There was this
whoosh of water.

00:32:07.930 --> 00:32:09.134
(SCREAMS)

00:32:09.269 --> 00:32:10.996
And I got sucked
into a filtering system.

00:32:11.132 --> 00:32:12.499
Help! (GRUNTS)

00:32:12.634 --> 00:32:14.597
But then I heard
this explosion.

00:32:14.733 --> 00:32:17.009
(RUMBLING)
(EMBER SCREAMING)

00:32:18.007 --> 00:32:19.143
(WADE SCREAMS)

00:32:19.279 --> 00:32:21.143
That's how I ended up
at your place.

00:32:21.279 --> 00:32:24.113
Oh, flame!
My temper caused this.

00:32:24.248 --> 00:32:25.507
So, we're searching
for water

00:32:25.642 --> 00:32:27.312
somewhere in a canal?

00:32:27.447 --> 00:32:29.118
Those canals go everywhere.

00:32:29.254 --> 00:32:30.655
It's why tracking down
that leak

00:32:30.790 --> 00:32:32.214
has been so dang hard.

00:32:32.349 --> 00:32:33.355
The roof.

00:32:35.188 --> 00:32:36.193
(GRUNTS)

00:32:38.457 --> 00:32:40.427
(GRUNTS)
(YELPS)

00:32:40.562 --> 00:32:43.035
(GRUNTS) You might
want to step back.

00:32:43.602 --> 00:32:45.004
(GRUNTS)

00:32:45.938 --> 00:32:48.073
(CAPTIVATING MUSIC PLAYING)

00:32:49.269 --> 00:32:50.838
Holy dew drop!

00:32:50.973 --> 00:32:52.704
Shh. Get in.

00:32:53.470 --> 00:32:54.475
(WADE GRUNTS)

00:32:55.439 --> 00:32:56.873
(FIRE ROARS)

00:33:04.155 --> 00:33:06.223
(CAPTIVATING MUSIC CONTINUES)

00:33:07.418 --> 00:33:09.121
(WATER BUBBLING)

00:33:09.256 --> 00:33:10.359
(STEAM HISSING)

00:33:18.303 --> 00:33:19.995
Okay, that's where
I got sucked in.

00:33:21.533 --> 00:33:23.537
More water. Go that way.

00:33:28.708 --> 00:33:30.706
(CHUCKLING)
Yeah, right there.

00:33:30.842 --> 00:33:32.851
Mm. (LAUGHS) Oh!
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

00:33:32.987 --> 00:33:34.285
Nothing weird
going on here.

00:33:34.420 --> 00:33:36.385
(IN SINGSONG)
Uh, just a little
pruning.

00:33:40.320 --> 00:33:42.325
(BOTH LAUGHING)

00:33:44.896 --> 00:33:46.098
(EMBER SNIFFS)

00:33:51.565 --> 00:33:53.672
So, uh, what do you do
at the shop?

00:33:53.808 --> 00:33:55.569
If you don't mind me asking.

00:33:55.704 --> 00:33:57.835
EMBER: My dad's retiring
and I'll be taking over.

00:33:58.237 --> 00:33:59.243
Someday.

00:34:00.473 --> 00:34:01.742
When I'm ready. (SIGHS)

00:34:01.877 --> 00:34:03.648
WADE: It must be nice knowing
what you're gonna do.

00:34:03.783 --> 00:34:04.816
After my dad passed,

00:34:04.952 --> 00:34:06.647
I got all, "What's the point?"

00:34:06.782 --> 00:34:09.448
Now I just go
from one job
to the next.

00:34:09.583 --> 00:34:11.449
There's a word
in Firish.

00:34:11.585 --> 00:34:13.024
(SPEAKING FIRISH) Tishok.

00:34:13.160 --> 00:34:15.058
It means embrace
the light while it burns

00:34:15.194 --> 00:34:16.953
because it won't
always last forever.

00:34:17.888 --> 00:34:21.725
(HALTINGLY)
Tee-shook.

00:34:21.861 --> 00:34:23.399
Or something like that.
(CHUCKLES)

00:34:28.809 --> 00:34:30.175
You okay?
Yeah.

00:34:30.908 --> 00:34:32.704
You sure?

00:34:32.839 --> 00:34:36.210
It's just,
that building over there,

00:34:36.346 --> 00:34:38.577
that's Garden
Central Station.

00:34:38.712 --> 00:34:40.944
When I was a kid,
my dad took me there

00:34:41.079 --> 00:34:43.320
because they had
a Vivisteria tree.

00:34:44.288 --> 00:34:47.053
I'd always wanted to see one.

00:34:47.188 --> 00:34:50.019
It's the only flower that can
thrive in any environment.

00:34:51.798 --> 00:34:53.022
Fire included.

00:34:54.065 --> 00:34:55.860
I was so excited.

00:34:55.995 --> 00:34:58.203
But they said our fire
was too dangerous,

00:34:59.138 --> 00:35:00.534
and they wouldn't let us in.

00:35:00.669 --> 00:35:03.602
(SHOUTS IN FIRISH)
Go back to Fire Land.

00:35:03.738 --> 00:35:05.307
EMBER: My dad
was so angry...

00:35:05.443 --> 00:35:07.472
Burn somewhere else!
Get outta here!

00:35:07.608 --> 00:35:09.311
EMBER: ...and embarrassed.

00:35:09.446 --> 00:35:11.415
The building flooded
a few years later.

00:35:11.550 --> 00:35:14.483
So, I missed my one chance
to see a Vivisteria.

00:35:18.652 --> 00:35:20.687
You must have
been so scared.

00:35:22.761 --> 00:35:23.888
I was.

00:35:25.328 --> 00:35:27.492
(GROANS) How do
you do that?

00:35:27.627 --> 00:35:29.399
Do what?
Draw people in?

00:35:29.535 --> 00:35:31.500
You got a whole stadium
to connect with you.

00:35:31.636 --> 00:35:34.566
I... I can't even connect
with one customer.

00:35:34.701 --> 00:35:36.699
My stupid temper
always kicks in.

00:35:36.835 --> 00:35:39.474
I guess I just say
what I feel.

00:35:39.610 --> 00:35:41.376
And I don't think
a temper is so bad.

00:35:41.512 --> 00:35:43.541
Sometimes when I lose
my temper,

00:35:43.676 --> 00:35:44.975
I think it's just me trying

00:35:45.110 --> 00:35:46.982
to tell me something
I'm not ready to hear.

00:35:47.117 --> 00:35:48.319
That's ridiculous.

00:35:49.150 --> 00:35:50.145
Maybe.

00:35:50.823 --> 00:35:51.920
Hey, there.

00:35:52.056 --> 00:35:53.225
Put us down there.

00:35:54.291 --> 00:35:56.261
(THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING)

00:35:58.997 --> 00:36:00.265
That's not right.

00:36:02.627 --> 00:36:03.701
(SMACKS LIPS)

00:36:03.836 --> 00:36:04.761
Motor oil.

00:36:04.896 --> 00:36:06.568
Yup, this
is the source.

00:36:07.866 --> 00:36:08.964
Why is there
no water?

00:36:09.099 --> 00:36:10.505
Because the doors
are broken.

00:36:10.640 --> 00:36:12.510
This is supposed
to catch spill over

00:36:12.646 --> 00:36:14.213
from those
main canals and...
(SHIP HORN BLOWS)

00:36:19.677 --> 00:36:21.044
Run for your life!

00:36:23.549 --> 00:36:24.513
(WADE GRUNTS)

00:36:24.648 --> 00:36:25.783
(SCREAMS)

00:36:25.918 --> 00:36:28.117
Help! (SCREAMING)
(WATER RUMBLING)

00:36:28.662 --> 00:36:29.960
Uh...

00:36:30.096 --> 00:36:31.553
(GRUNTS)
Grab this!

00:36:31.688 --> 00:36:33.027
(GRUNTING)

00:36:33.162 --> 00:36:34.431
(GRUNTING)

00:36:35.230 --> 00:36:36.224
(WADE GRUNTS)

00:36:36.593 --> 00:36:38.100
(PANTING)

00:36:38.235 --> 00:36:40.232
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

00:36:40.367 --> 00:36:41.405
EMBER: Firetown.

00:36:50.345 --> 00:36:51.943
Catch!
(GRUNTS)

00:36:52.345 --> 00:36:53.318
(GROANS)

00:36:57.856 --> 00:36:58.818
(GRUNTS)

00:37:01.695 --> 00:37:02.756
(GRUNTING)

00:37:13.333 --> 00:37:14.368
(GRUNTS)

00:37:14.503 --> 00:37:16.605
