It worked!

00:50:03.408 --> 00:50:05.034
I'll have Gale
come by
right after work.

00:50:05.169 --> 00:50:07.043
I'll let you know
the second
I hear anything.

00:50:07.179 --> 00:50:08.538
You think this will be
good enough for her?

00:50:08.674 --> 00:50:10.573
Honestly,
it's hard to know.

00:50:10.708 --> 00:50:12.182
She could go
either way.

00:50:12.650 --> 00:50:13.645
Oh.

00:50:14.810 --> 00:50:16.681
Here. I saved this for you.

00:50:18.382 --> 00:50:19.647
It's special.

00:50:19.782 --> 00:50:21.752
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

00:50:24.894 --> 00:50:26.625
(SOFT TINKLING)

00:50:28.363 --> 00:50:30.398
(BERNIE COUGHING)
(GASPS)

00:50:33.664 --> 00:50:35.401
Ashfa, you okay?

00:50:35.537 --> 00:50:38.633
Yes, yes.
Just too much to fix.

00:50:38.769 --> 00:50:39.944
I'll take
care of it.

00:50:40.079 --> 00:50:42.413
You need to rest,
and that's an order.

00:50:42.549 --> 00:50:43.580
Yes, ma'am.

00:50:43.715 --> 00:50:45.248
(BOTH LAUGH)

00:50:46.347 --> 00:50:48.847
Ember, I see
a change in you.

00:50:48.983 --> 00:50:49.951
Happier,

00:50:50.086 --> 00:50:51.747
calmer with customers

00:50:51.882 --> 00:50:55.255
and with that
food inspector.

00:50:55.390 --> 00:50:57.557
Always putting
shop first.

00:50:58.756 --> 00:51:00.956
You prove
I can trust you.

00:51:04.603 --> 00:51:06.269
(COUGHING)

00:51:07.402 --> 00:51:10.236
I'm so lucky
I have you.

00:51:10.372 --> 00:51:12.704
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC CONTINUES)

00:51:22.380 --> 00:51:23.882
(SNORES, SNIFFS)

00:51:24.018 --> 00:51:24.951
Love?

00:51:25.087 --> 00:51:26.080
(BELL JINGLES)

00:51:28.485 --> 00:51:30.252
(ENGINE REVS)

00:51:30.387 --> 00:51:32.361
(SNIFFING)

00:51:35.663 --> 00:51:37.993
(INTRIGUING FUSION
MUSIC PLAYING)

00:51:44.770 --> 00:51:46.900
Ember, you found it.
Everything okay?

00:51:47.036 --> 00:51:48.110
Please tell me
that you have

00:51:48.245 --> 00:51:49.312
some good news
from Gale.

00:51:49.447 --> 00:51:51.509
I'm getting really worried
about my dad.

00:51:51.644 --> 00:51:52.975
This has to break
my way.

00:51:53.111 --> 00:51:54.579
Yeah,
I haven't heard
from her yet,

00:51:54.715 --> 00:51:56.484
but she swore
she'd call tonight.

00:51:56.619 --> 00:51:58.855
Actually, my family
stopped by for dinner.

00:51:58.991 --> 00:52:00.014
You want
to come up

00:52:00.150 --> 00:52:01.152
and wait
for the call
together?

00:52:01.287 --> 00:52:02.654
Your family?

00:52:02.789 --> 00:52:05.622
(CINDER SNIFFING)
(GRUNTING DISAPPROVINGLY)

00:52:05.757 --> 00:52:08.331
EMBER: Um...
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

00:52:08.467 --> 00:52:10.799
Okay. I'll...
I'll come up
for a bit.

00:52:10.934 --> 00:52:12.035
(GASPS, GROWLS)

00:52:12.170 --> 00:52:13.869
I'm sorry,
you live here?

00:52:14.004 --> 00:52:14.970
It's my mom's place.

00:52:15.106 --> 00:52:16.097
EMBER:
Oh, my gosh!

00:52:17.974 --> 00:52:18.933
(CHUCKLES)

00:52:19.068 --> 00:52:20.943
I'm afraid
I can't let you in.

00:52:21.079 --> 00:52:22.771
Residents
and guests only.

00:52:22.906 --> 00:52:25.876
Ah! Okay.
I understand.

00:52:27.413 --> 00:52:29.252
(CINDER GRUNTING)

00:52:29.388 --> 00:52:31.419
You're surprisingly
good at your job.

00:52:31.555 --> 00:52:33.581
You're surprisingly
fast for your age.

00:52:33.716 --> 00:52:35.658
You have no idea.

00:52:35.794 --> 00:52:37.395
(WIND HOWLS)

00:52:37.530 --> 00:52:40.855
Ember! Oh,
I'm so excited
to finally meet you.

00:52:40.990 --> 00:52:43.366
Do we hug,
or wave, or...?

00:52:43.502 --> 00:52:45.034
Don't want
to put you out.
(CHUCKLES)

00:52:45.169 --> 00:52:47.031
Um, a hello
is fine.

00:52:47.167 --> 00:52:49.566
Hardly.
Wade hasn't stopped
talking about you

00:52:49.702 --> 00:52:50.798
since the day
you met.

00:52:50.933 --> 00:52:52.734
The boy
is smitten.
Mom.

00:52:52.869 --> 00:52:54.573
Oh, come on.
I'm your mother.

00:52:54.709 --> 00:52:56.543
I know
when something's
lighting you up.

00:52:56.678 --> 00:52:59.342
I just didn't know
she'd be so smoky.

00:52:59.477 --> 00:53:00.409
(FAKE-COUGHS)

00:53:00.544 --> 00:53:01.744
(BOTH LAUGHING)

00:53:01.880 --> 00:53:03.112
(EMBER LAUGHS
UNCOMFORTABLY)

00:53:03.248 --> 00:53:05.016
Come this way,
meet the rest
of the family.

00:53:05.152 --> 00:53:06.257
(GASPS)

00:53:06.392 --> 00:53:08.721
(MELLOW JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)
(WATER LAPPING)

00:53:09.829 --> 00:53:11.185
Hmm.
Oh.

00:53:17.533 --> 00:53:18.928
Oh, honey,
you won't believe

00:53:19.064 --> 00:53:20.035
what your
baby niece
did today.

00:53:20.171 --> 00:53:22.002
She...
She smiled.

00:53:22.137 --> 00:53:23.905
No, she didn't.

00:53:24.041 --> 00:53:25.606
(BOTH SOBBING)

00:53:26.474 --> 00:53:27.575
WADE'S MOM:
Yeah.

00:53:28.343 --> 00:53:29.376
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

00:53:29.512 --> 00:53:31.040
Hey, everyone,
this is Ember.

00:53:31.442 --> 00:53:32.514
Hey!

00:53:32.649 --> 00:53:34.811
That's my brother Alan
and his wife Eddy.

00:53:34.946 --> 00:53:36.716
Hi.
And we got
two kids

00:53:36.851 --> 00:53:38.150
that are swimmin'
around here somewhere.

00:53:38.285 --> 00:53:40.715
Marco! Polo!

00:53:40.850 --> 00:53:42.253
What?
(BOTH LAUGHING)

00:53:42.388 --> 00:53:43.652
Hi, Uncle Wade!

00:53:43.787 --> 00:53:44.961
Do you die
if you fall

00:53:45.097 --> 00:53:46.524
in water?
Whoa!

00:53:46.660 --> 00:53:48.527
Marco!
Kids, (CHUCKLES) right?

00:53:48.662 --> 00:53:49.924
(MARCO GRUNTS)
Don't hate us.

00:53:50.060 --> 00:53:51.863
Anyway, that's my
little sib, Lake,

00:53:51.998 --> 00:53:53.734
and her girlfriend, Ghibli.
GHIBLI: 'Sup!

00:53:53.870 --> 00:53:56.270
They're student
s at Element City
School for the Arts.

00:53:56.406 --> 00:53:57.734
Yeah. Following
in Mom's wake.

00:53:57.870 --> 00:53:59.870
Oh, nonsense.
I'm just an architect.

00:54:00.006 --> 00:54:02.003
The real artist
is my brother, Harold.

00:54:02.139 --> 00:54:05.075
Oh, I just dabble
in watercolors.

00:54:05.210 --> 00:54:07.781
Or as we like
to call them,
"colors."

00:54:07.917 --> 00:54:10.680
Oh, don't listen to him.
He's a wonderful painter.

00:54:10.815 --> 00:54:11.982
One of his paintings
just got

00:54:12.117 --> 00:54:14.089
in the Element City Museum's
permanent collection.

00:54:14.224 --> 00:54:15.822
Wow, that is so cool.

00:54:15.958 --> 00:54:18.260
My only talent
is "Clean up
on aisle four."

00:54:18.395 --> 00:54:19.628
(CHUCKLES)
Talk about being modest.

00:54:19.764 --> 00:54:21.759
Ember's got
an incredible
creative flame.

00:54:21.895 --> 00:54:23.258
I've never seen
anything like it.

00:54:23.393 --> 00:54:28.168
I just have to say
that you speak
so well and clear.

00:54:28.303 --> 00:54:29.465
(CHUCKLES FORCEDLY)

00:54:29.601 --> 00:54:30.668
Yeah, it's amazing

00:54:30.803 --> 00:54:31.941
what talking
in the same language

00:54:32.077 --> 00:54:33.307
your entire life can do.

00:54:33.442 --> 00:54:34.939
Oh!
Uh, hey, Ember,

00:54:35.074 --> 00:54:36.874
did, uh,
Wadey here
ever tell you

00:54:37.009 --> 00:54:38.810
that he's deathly
afraid of sponges?

00:54:38.945 --> 00:54:41.517
No.
WADE:
I was traumatized.

00:54:42.754 --> 00:54:44.016
Huh?

00:54:44.151 --> 00:54:45.147
Huh.

00:54:45.858 --> 00:54:46.852
(SCREAMS)

00:54:49.126 --> 00:54:51.187
(ALL LAUGHING)

00:54:51.322 --> 00:54:53.295
I still can't
use a sponge
around him.

00:54:53.430 --> 00:54:55.192
I was stuck
in there
for hours.

00:54:55.328 --> 00:54:56.362
(LAUGHS)

00:54:56.498 --> 00:54:58.435
Oh.
Alan! That was new.

00:54:58.570 --> 00:55:00.837
ALAN: My bad.
I'm all whirlpools tonight.

00:55:00.973 --> 00:55:01.928
I can fix it.

00:55:02.064 --> 00:55:04.034
(INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING)

00:55:05.702 --> 00:55:06.833
(SQUELCHING)

00:55:06.969 --> 00:55:08.478
(INHALES DEEPLY, BLOWS)

00:55:22.125 --> 00:55:23.460
Oh, um...

00:55:24.324 --> 00:55:25.319
Sorry.

00:55:26.262 --> 00:55:28.227
That was incredible!

00:55:28.363 --> 00:55:29.661
(ALL EXCLAIM)

00:55:29.796 --> 00:55:31.033
It's just
melted glass.

00:55:31.168 --> 00:55:32.465
Just melted glass?

00:55:32.601 --> 00:55:33.864
Every building
in the new city

00:55:34.000 --> 00:55:36.067
is built from
just melted glass.

00:55:36.203 --> 00:55:38.233
Oh, no, you have to do
something with that talent.

00:55:39.643 --> 00:55:42.237
See, I told you,
you're special.

00:55:42.872 --> 00:55:44.041
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

00:55:44.876 --> 00:55:46.411
(BUBBLING)
(GASPS)

00:55:46.546 --> 00:55:47.782
Ooh, thought bubble.

00:55:47.918 --> 00:55:50.979
Maybe after
dinner we play
The Crying Game?

00:55:51.114 --> 00:55:52.487
(CLAMORING)
Yes, yes, yes.

00:55:52.622 --> 00:55:54.925
Let me guess,
you try to cry?

00:55:55.060 --> 00:55:57.227
We try not to cry.

00:55:57.362 --> 00:55:59.353
You have
one minute. Go!

00:56:01.361 --> 00:56:04.329
1979. November. You were...
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYS)

00:56:04.464 --> 00:56:06.103
(BAWLING)

00:56:06.238 --> 00:56:07.328
(CHEERING)
(GROANING)

00:56:07.463 --> 00:56:10.798
Never got a chance
to say goodbye to Nana.

00:56:10.934 --> 00:56:12.602
(CONTINUES BAWLING)

00:56:12.737 --> 00:56:13.935
Damn, you're good.

00:56:14.070 --> 00:56:16.414
Okay, Ember,
Wade, you're up.

00:56:18.043 --> 00:56:19.779
Yeah, this is
almost unfair

00:56:19.914 --> 00:56:22.579
because I have
literally never cried.

00:56:22.714 --> 00:56:24.111
You got no chance.

00:56:24.246 --> 00:56:25.786
Sounds like
a challenge.

00:56:26.684 --> 00:56:28.021
Ready, go!

00:56:28.157 --> 00:56:30.927
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYS)
Butterfly, windshield wipers,

00:56:31.063 --> 00:56:32.887
half a butterfly.

00:56:33.023 --> 00:56:35.026
(BOTH SNIFFLING)
(SOBS)

00:56:37.727 --> 00:56:39.060
Okay.

00:56:39.195 --> 00:56:40.996
An old man
on his deathbed

00:56:41.132 --> 00:56:43.405
remembers the summer
he fell in love.

00:56:43.540 --> 00:56:44.604
She was out
of his league

00:56:44.740 --> 00:56:46.337
and he was young
and scared.

00:56:46.472 --> 00:56:47.608
(SNIFFLES)

00:56:47.743 --> 00:56:49.078
He let her go,
thinking surely

00:56:49.214 --> 00:56:50.275
summer would come again.

00:56:50.411 --> 00:56:52.245
(SNIFFLING)

00:56:52.381 --> 00:56:53.374
It never did.

00:56:55.044 --> 00:56:56.718
Almost out of time.

00:56:59.859 --> 00:57:01.657
Ember,

00:57:01.792 --> 00:57:04.561
when I met you,
I thought I was drowning.

00:57:05.690 --> 00:57:07.554
But that light,

00:57:07.689 --> 00:57:11.535
that light inside you
has made me feel so alive.

00:57:13.605 --> 00:57:16.199
And all I want now
is to be near it.

00:57:17.603 --> 00:57:18.608
Near you.

00:57:19.342 --> 00:57:20.478
Together.

00:57:21.512 --> 00:57:23.877
(DREAMY NEW-AGE
MUSIC PLAYING)

00:57:35.225 --> 00:57:36.186
(WHOOSHES)

00:57:42.100 --> 00:57:43.061
(SIZZLES)

00:57:44.596 --> 00:57:46.570
ALL: Aw.

00:57:47.633 --> 00:57:49.001
(PHONE RINGING)

00:57:50.441 --> 00:57:52.167
Hello?
Gale, hi.

00:57:52.303 --> 00:57:54.970
Glass? You repaired it
with glass?

00:57:55.105 --> 00:57:56.107
Hold the storm.
Hey!

00:57:57.447 --> 00:57:58.682
(GRUNTS)
(CLANKS)

00:57:58.818 --> 00:58:01.847
Tempered glass.
Solid as a rock,
I like it.

00:58:01.982 --> 00:58:04.280
Consider the tickets
cancelled.

00:58:05.983 --> 00:58:07.551
We did it?
Yup!

00:58:07.686 --> 00:58:09.619
(BOTH LAUGHING)

00:58:09.755 --> 00:58:12.187
Awesome! Whoo!

00:58:12.323 --> 00:58:13.923
Oh.
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)
Oh. Um...

00:58:14.059 --> 00:58:15.826
(LAUGHS)
(WADE GROANS)

00:58:15.962 --> 00:58:17.359
Thank you,
Mrs. Ripple.

00:58:17.960 --> 00:58:19.097
This was...

00:58:19.865 --> 00:58:20.861
This was really great.

00:58:20.997 --> 00:58:22.200
Yeah, it was.

00:58:22.335 --> 00:58:24.539
And I mean
what I said
about your talent.

00:58:24.674 --> 00:58:25.841
I have a friend
who runs

00:58:25.976 --> 00:58:28.073
the best
glassmaking firm
in the world.

00:58:28.208 --> 00:58:30.512
During dinner,
I slipped out
and I made a call

00:58:30.647 --> 00:58:32.812
and I told her
about you.

00:58:32.947 --> 00:58:34.177
They're looking
for an intern.

00:58:34.312 --> 00:58:36.415
It could be
an amazing opportunity.

00:58:36.550 --> 00:58:37.551
For real?

00:58:37.687 --> 00:58:38.652
It's a long way
from the city,

00:58:38.788 --> 00:58:40.652
but it would be
an incredible start.

00:58:40.788 --> 00:58:43.252
You have a bright future.

00:58:43.388 --> 00:58:46.190
Look at me,
I have an original Ember.

00:58:46.857 --> 00:58:48.121
(CHUCKLES)

00:58:48.257 --> 00:58:49.864
Hold up,
I'll walk you out.

00:58:51.596 --> 00:58:53.961
(BREATHLESSLY)
I'm afraid
you're going to have

00:58:54.097 --> 00:58:55.537
to wait out here, ma'am.

00:58:55.673 --> 00:58:58.041
And I'm afraid...
(PANTING)

00:58:58.176 --> 00:58:59.577
I will throw up.

00:59:00.706 --> 00:59:01.711
(CINDER GROANS)

00:59:05.007 --> 00:59:06.279
(GROANS)

00:59:06.414 --> 00:59:07.513
(BURBLES)

00:59:07.649 --> 00:59:08.682
WADE:
Ember.

00:59:08.817 --> 00:59:10.150
Ember, hold up,
what's going on?

00:59:10.286 --> 00:59:12.112
I can't believe
she basically
offered me a job.

00:59:12.247 --> 00:59:14.083
I know!
Could be cool.

00:59:14.218 --> 00:59:15.151
Yeah,
super cool, Wade.

00:59:15.286 --> 00:59:16.483
I could move out
and make glass

00:59:16.619 --> 00:59:18.660
in a faraway city.
Do whatever I want.

00:59:18.796 --> 00:59:20.794
I don't understand.
I'm going home.

00:59:20.929 --> 00:59:21.992
Fine, then
I'm going with you.

00:59:22.127 --> 00:59:23.132
(EMBER GROANS)
(TIRES SCREECH)

00:59:23.268 --> 00:59:24.925
(PEOPLE YELP)

00:59:25.060 --> 00:59:26.935
A Water guy?

00:59:27.070 --> 00:59:29.365
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)
(BIKE ACCELERATING)

00:59:31.843 --> 00:59:34.807
Look, my mom
was just trying
to be helpful.

00:59:34.943 --> 00:59:36.108
She doesn't know
how excited

00:59:36.243 --> 00:59:37.975
you are to run the shop.
(SHOUTS IN FRUSTRATION)

00:59:38.111 --> 00:59:40.080
What is the matter?
Nothing!

00:59:40.215 --> 00:59:42.314
Yeah? 'Cause we're going,
like, a thousand...

00:59:42.450 --> 00:59:43.749
Bus!

00:59:43.884 --> 00:59:45.183
(TIRES SCREECH)
(WADE YELPS)

00:59:47.120 --> 00:59:49.020
You don't know me,
Wade. Okay?

00:59:49.155 --> 00:59:50.754
So stop pretending
like you do.

00:59:50.890 --> 00:59:51.961
What is this about?

00:59:52.097 --> 00:59:53.089
Nothing.

00:59:53.224 --> 00:59:54.992
Everything.
I don't know. It's...

00:59:55.127 --> 00:59:57.327
(CLICKS)
(TIRES SCREECH)

00:59:58.897 --> 01:00:00.332
(EMBER PANTS)

01:00:00.468 --> 01:00:03.170
I don't think
I actually do want
to run the shop.

01:00:03.306 --> 01:00:04.334
Okay?

01:00:06.573 --> 01:00:09.174
That's what
my temper has been
trying to tell me.

01:00:11.579 --> 01:00:12.782
I'm trapped.

01:00:15.379 --> 01:00:17.453
(SIGHS) You know
what's crazy?

01:00:17.589 --> 01:00:18.951
Even when
I was a kid,

01:00:19.086 --> 01:00:20.484
I would pray
to the Blue Flame

01:00:20.619 --> 01:00:23.450
to be good enough to fill
my father's shoes someday

01:00:23.586 --> 01:00:25.619
because this place
is his dream.

01:00:26.521 --> 01:00:28.490
But I never
once asked...

01:00:30.269 --> 01:00:31.834
what I wanted to do.

01:00:33.172 --> 01:00:34.802
(SIGHS)

01:00:34.938 --> 01:00:37.372
I think that's
because deep down,

01:00:37.508 --> 01:00:39.336
I knew it didn't matter.

01:00:41.104 --> 01:00:42.270
Because the only way

01:00:42.405 --> 01:00:44.308
to repay
a sacrifice so big

01:00:45.641 --> 01:00:48.180
is by sacrificing
your life too.

01:00:50.446 --> 01:00:51.649
CINDER: Ember!
(GASPS)

01:00:51.784 --> 01:00:53.390
Don't move.

01:00:53.525 --> 01:00:54.553
Oh, blaze!
My mother.

01:00:54.688 --> 01:00:55.724
(CINDER PANTING)

01:00:55.859 --> 01:00:57.860
(FOOTSTEPS CLANKING
ON STAIRS)

01:01:03.263 --> 01:01:05.263
Mom, it's okay.
He's just a friend.

01:01:05.632 --> 01:01:06.729
Si...

01:01:06.865 --> 01:01:07.834
Silence!

01:01:07.969 --> 01:01:09.969
(GASPS)
I could smell you

01:01:10.104 --> 01:01:12.168
from over there.
Oh, you stink.

01:01:12.303 --> 01:01:13.709
What are you
talking about?

01:01:13.845 --> 01:01:16.705
CINDER: You know
what I'm talking about.

01:01:16.841 --> 01:01:18.405
(SNIFFS)

01:01:18.541 --> 01:01:21.276
You're smelling
love on me?

01:01:21.411 --> 01:01:24.114
If your father
find out...

01:01:24.249 --> 01:01:28.415
Fire and Water
cannot be together.

01:01:28.550 --> 01:01:30.761
I prove it.
Come with me.

01:01:33.732 --> 01:01:34.730
I splash this
on your heart

01:01:34.865 --> 01:01:35.865
to bring love
to the surface.

01:01:36.828 --> 01:01:38.164
(SIZZLES)

01:01:38.831 --> 01:01:39.836
(GRUNTS)

01:01:40.404 --> 01:01:42.005
(SLURPS) Mmm!

01:01:42.140 --> 01:01:44.934
And then you
must light these
with your fire,

01:01:45.070 --> 01:01:46.403
and I read
the smoke.

01:01:47.675 --> 01:01:48.669
(SNIFFS)

01:01:49.677 --> 01:01:51.078
(SIZZLES)

01:01:55.212 --> 01:01:57.216
(PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:01:58.547 --> 01:02:01.154
See, Ember?
It cannot be.

01:02:04.824 --> 01:02:05.961
Actually...

01:02:08.159 --> 01:02:09.129
What are you doing?

01:02:14.196 --> 01:02:16.202
(SLOSHING)

01:02:21.712 --> 01:02:23.671
(INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING)

01:02:27.484 --> 01:02:28.577
(SIZZLES)

01:02:38.089 --> 01:02:39.258
(SNIFFS DEEPLY)

01:02:42.433 --> 01:02:43.390
BERNIE: Cinder?

01:02:43.526 --> 01:02:44.491
Who down there?
(ALL GASP)

01:02:44.627 --> 01:02:46.265
It's my dad.
You have to go.

01:02:48.607 --> 01:02:50.236
Wait, are we a match? (YELPS)

01:02:50.371 --> 01:02:52.837
What's going on?
I wake up
and nobody upstairs.

01:02:52.972 --> 01:02:53.940
It was just me.

01:02:54.075 --> 01:02:55.340
(DOOR SHUTS)
(WADE GRUNTS)

01:02:55.476 --> 01:02:58.175
I was double-checking
the locks. (CHUCKLES)

01:02:58.310 --> 01:02:59.709
And Mom
came down and...

01:02:59.844 --> 01:03:04.149
Yes, and we,
uh, began looking
at this door.

01:03:04.284 --> 01:03:05.985
We don't talk
about this door enough.

01:03:06.121 --> 01:03:07.149
(WHISPERS)
Pull it together.

01:03:07.285 --> 01:03:08.956
Well, since
you're awake,

01:03:09.091 --> 01:03:10.661
I was gonna
tell you tomorrow,

01:03:10.796 --> 01:03:13.859
but I'm too
excited to sleep.

01:03:13.994 --> 01:03:16.424
In two days,
I retire.

01:03:16.559 --> 01:03:18.125
Ooh.
(GASPS) Oh, Bernie.

01:03:18.260 --> 01:03:19.264
Two days?

01:03:19.399 --> 01:03:22.130
Yes. We're going
to throw big party.

01:03:22.265 --> 01:03:23.663
A grand reopening.

01:03:23.799 --> 01:03:26.041
That way I can tell
whole world

01:03:26.176 --> 01:03:28.678
my daughter take over.
(CINDER LAUGHING)

01:03:28.813 --> 01:03:31.344
And I have gift
for you.

01:03:31.479 --> 01:03:34.418
I've had this for a while,
but after our talk,

01:03:34.553 --> 01:03:37.079
I know now
is the time.

01:03:37.215 --> 01:03:38.789
Before I give it to you,

01:03:38.924 --> 01:03:42.349
I need you to understand
what it means to me.

01:03:42.484 --> 01:03:43.724
(SOLEMN MUSIC PLAYING)

01:03:43.859 --> 01:03:45.225
When I left Fire Land,

01:03:47.329 --> 01:03:49.867
I gave my father
the Ba Kso...

01:03:51.932 --> 01:03:52.903
the big bow.

01:03:55.370 --> 01:03:57.908
It is the highest
form of respect.

01:04:02.404 --> 01:04:04.074
But my father

01:04:04.210 --> 01:04:06.510
did not return the bow.

01:04:07.644 --> 01:04:09.920
Did not give me
his blessing.

01:04:10.889 --> 01:04:13.480
He say,
if we leave Fire Land,

01:04:13.615 --> 01:04:15.852
we will lose who we are.

01:04:15.988 --> 01:04:17.651
(CRYING)

01:04:17.787 --> 01:04:20.058
They never got
to see all of this.

01:04:20.194 --> 01:04:21.325
They didn't
get to see

01:04:21.461 --> 01:04:25.030
that I never forgot
we are Fire.

01:04:25.165 --> 01:04:28.596
This is burden
I still carry.

01:04:28.732 --> 01:04:31.239
Ember,
it is important
that you know

01:04:31.374 --> 01:04:35.470
you have my blessing
every day you come in here.

01:04:35.606 --> 01:04:38.410
So I have this
made for you.

01:04:39.243 --> 01:04:40.709
Wow, Ashfa.

01:04:42.216 --> 01:04:44.413
It's gonna be
big, bright.

01:04:44.548 --> 01:04:46.247
Everyone's gonna
see this.

01:04:46.382 --> 01:04:48.418
"Ember's Fireplace."

01:04:48.554 --> 01:04:50.889
We unveil it
at grand reopening.

01:04:51.024 --> 01:04:52.422
(LAUGHS BOISTEROUSLY)

01:04:52.558 --> 01:04:55.196
Come, Bernie.
You need your rest.

01:04:57.766 --> 01:04:59.101
(BERNIE COUGHS)

01:04:59.868 --> 01:05:01.829
(SIGN BUZZING)

01:05:04.102 --> 01:05:05.833
(SNIFFS, CRYING)

01:05:09.207 --> 01:05:10.739
(SHIP HORN BLOWS)

01:05:17.379 --> 01:05:18.714
(CRACKING)

01:05:20.557 --> 01:05:24.052
Ember, so,
what'd your mom say
about our reading?

01:05:24.188 --> 01:05:25.223
Nothing.

01:05:25.359 --> 01:05:26.920
Look, I have
a gift for you.

01:05:30.336 --> 01:05:34.002
And you came
all the way here
to give it to me?

01:05:34.138 --> 01:05:35.973
Wait, why are you
giving me gifts?

01:05:37.568 --> 01:05:40.308
Oh, no.
No, no, no, no, no, no.

01:05:40.443 --> 01:05:42.438
Hold on, I think I have
something to show you.

01:05:42.573 --> 01:05:43.903
Just give me
two seconds.

01:05:44.039 --> 01:05:45.609
And you're gonna need
a pair of boots.

01:05:47.643 --> 01:05:49.347
(MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

01:05:49.482 --> 01:05:51.585
Wade, what are we
doing here?

01:05:51.720 --> 01:05:52.847
Just wait.

01:06:01.297 --> 01:06:02.630
Why do
they even
have these?

01:06:02.766 --> 01:06:03.726
Eh, who knows?

01:06:06.934 --> 01:06:08.071
(SIGN CLATTERS)

01:06:10.975 --> 01:06:13.502
Hey,
it's my favorite
fireball.

01:06:13.637 --> 01:06:15.836
Hey, Gale.
What's going on?

01:06:15.972 --> 01:06:18.540
I know you think
you have to end this,

01:06:18.675 --> 01:06:20.048
but that
flooded tunnel,

01:06:20.183 --> 01:06:21.878
it goes
to the main terminal.

01:06:22.014 --> 01:06:23.283
Okay.

01:06:23.419 --> 01:06:25.484
Do you still want
to see a Vivisteria?

01:06:26.821 --> 01:06:28.216
Gale?

01:06:28.351 --> 01:06:30.225
(INHALES DEEPLY)

01:06:31.353 --> 01:06:33.360
(BLOWS)

01:06:36.660 --> 01:06:39.065
Wait, I'm supposed
to get in there?

01:06:39.201 --> 01:06:40.262
The air
should last...

01:06:40.398 --> 01:06:41.995
At least 20 minutes.

01:06:44.539 --> 01:06:46.337
They said
you couldn't
go in there.

01:06:46.472 --> 01:06:48.074
Why does anyone
get to tell you

01:06:48.210 --> 01:06:49.640
what you can do
in your life?

01:06:50.482 --> 01:06:51.404
(SIGHS)

01:06:51.539 --> 01:06:53.083
(WATER BUBBLING)

01:06:57.547 --> 01:06:58.845
(GRUNTS FEROCIOUSLY)

01:06:58.981 --> 01:07:01.355
(SOOTHING NEW-AGE
MUSIC PLAYING)

01:07:05.762 --> 01:07:06.954
(BLOWING)

01:07:10.196 --> 01:07:11.893
(HUFFING RAPIDLY)

01:07:12.395 --> 01:07:13.631
(EMBER GRUNTS)

01:07:17.168 --> 01:07:18.240
Whoa.

01:07:30.716 --> 01:07:33.123
(SOOTHING NEW-AGE
MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:07:34.518 --> 01:07:36.489
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

01:07:46.462 --> 01:07:47.929
(SLOSHING)

01:07:59.415 --> 01:08:01.811
(SOOTHING NEW-AGE
MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:08:08.554 --> 01:08:11.161
(SLOSHING)
(EMBER LAUGHS)

01:08:30.540 --> 01:08:32.479
(MUSIC BUILDS)

01:08:34.050 --> 01:08:35.812
(MUSIC TEMPO LOOSENS)

01:08:36.480 --> 01:08:38.012
A Vivisteria.

01:08:39.191 --> 01:08:41.455
(PEACEFUL NEW-AGE
MUSIC PLAYING)

01:08:56.773 --> 01:08:57.966
Whoa.

01:08:59.006 --> 01:09:01.002
(LAUGHING)

01:09:23.497 --> 01:09:24.795
(BUBBLING, SIZZLING)
(GASPS)

01:09:25.828 --> 01:09:26.794
(GRIMACES) Ouch.
Hey,

01:09:26.929 --> 01:09:28.062
you're running
out of air.

01:09:29.204 --> 01:09:31.208
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

01:09:35.012 --> 01:09:37.345
(EMBER GASPING RAPIDLY)

01:09:37.480 --> 01:09:40.074
Almost there. Try to breathe
slow and steady.

01:09:41.544 --> 01:09:42.884
(WADE GRUNTS)

01:09:43.019 --> 01:09:44.683
(EMBER GASPING)

01:09:46.923 --> 01:09:48.082
(BOTH GRUNT)

01:09:49.025 --> 01:09:50.788
(BOTH PANTING)

01:09:53.428 --> 01:09:54.698
I'm so sorry.
I should never...

01:09:54.833 --> 01:09:56.125
Are you kidding?

01:09:56.261 --> 01:09:59.093
That was amazing!
I finally saw
a Vivisteria!

01:10:00.028 --> 01:10:02.233
(GIGGLING)
It was inspiring.

01:10:02.368 --> 01:10:03.533
You were inspiring.

01:10:03.669 --> 01:10:05.099
(GENTLE NEW-AGE
MUSIC PLAYING)

01:10:07.673 --> 01:10:10.075
No. Wade, we...
we can't touch.

01:10:10.211 --> 01:10:11.347
Maybe we can.

01:10:11.749 --> 01:10:13.445
No.

01:10:13.581 --> 01:10:14.849
But can't
we just prove it?

01:10:14.984 --> 01:10:16.019
Prove what?

01:10:16.154 --> 01:10:17.512
Let's see
what happens,

01:10:17.648 --> 01:10:18.748
and if it's a disaster,

01:10:18.883 --> 01:10:20.386
then we'll know
this would never work.

01:10:20.522 --> 01:10:22.859
But it actually
could be a disaster.

01:10:22.994 --> 01:10:24.294
I could vaporize you.

01:10:24.429 --> 01:10:26.590
You... You could
extinguish me, and then...

01:10:26.725 --> 01:10:28.760
Let's...
Let's start small.

01:10:35.665 --> 01:10:37.771
(YELPS, GRUNTS)

01:10:37.907 --> 01:10:38.902
(SIGHS)

01:10:44.244 --> 01:10:45.175
(BUBBLING)

01:10:45.311 --> 01:10:46.344
(FIRE ROARS)

01:10:46.479 --> 01:10:48.084
(SIZZLES)
(GASPS)

01:10:48.219 --> 01:10:50.518
(GENTLE NEW-AGE
MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:11:03.758 --> 01:11:04.763
(SIZZLES)

01:11:07.930 --> 01:11:09.933
(BUBBLING)
(SIZZLING)

01:11:22.077 --> 01:11:24.420
(GENTLE NEW-AGE
MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:11:47.344 --> 01:11:49.676
(GENTLE NEW-AGE
MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:12:08.394 --> 01:12:10.026
I'm so lucky.

01:12:12.961 --> 01:12:13.961
(ELECTRICITY BUZZES)

01:12:14.096 --> 01:12:16.797
I'm so lucky
I have you.

01:12:16.932 --> 01:12:18.507
(ELECTRICITY BUZZING)

01:12:19.440 --> 01:12:20.468
(BUZZING INTENSIFIES)

01:12:20.604 --> 01:12:22.071
(GASPS)

01:12:23.773 --> 01:12:24.744
I have to go.

01:12:26.544 --> 01:12:27.917
Wait, what?

01:12:28.052 --> 01:12:29.310
Where are you going?

01:12:29.446 --> 01:12:31.087
EMBER: Back to my life
at the shop where I belong.

01:12:31.223 --> 01:12:32.254
I take over
tomorrow.

01:12:32.389 --> 01:12:33.718
Whoa, whoa,
whoa, hold up.

01:12:33.854 --> 01:12:36.259
You don't want that,
you said so yourself.

01:12:36.394 --> 01:12:37.752
It doesn't matter
what I want.

01:12:37.888 --> 01:12:39.423
Of course
it does.

01:12:39.558 --> 01:12:40.724
Listen. Listen.

01:12:40.859 --> 01:12:41.891
You've got
an opportunity

01:12:42.027 --> 01:12:43.732
to do something
you want with your life.

01:12:43.868 --> 01:12:45.092
"Want"?

01:12:45.227 --> 01:12:46.631
Yeah, that may work
in your rich kid,

01:12:46.767 --> 01:12:48.130
"follow your heart"
family,

01:12:48.266 --> 01:12:50.635
but getting to do
what you want is a luxury

01:12:50.770 --> 01:12:52.433
and not for people
like me.

01:12:52.568 --> 01:12:55.302
Why not?
Just tell your father
how you feel.

01:12:55.437 --> 01:12:57.444
This is too important.
Maybe he'll agree.

01:12:57.580 --> 01:12:59.614
(CHUCKLES SCORNFULLY)
Yeah.

01:13:00.885 --> 01:13:02.079
Funny.

01:13:02.214 --> 01:13:04.881
And this whole time,
I thought you
were so strong,

01:13:05.017 --> 01:13:08.455
but turns out
you're just afraid.

01:13:08.590 --> 01:13:10.786
Don't you dare
judge me.

01:13:10.921 --> 01:13:12.255
You don't know
what it's like

01:13:12.391 --> 01:13:14.497
to have parents
who gave up
everything for you.

01:13:16.231 --> 01:13:17.959
I'm Fire, Wade.

01:13:18.095 --> 01:13:19.763
I can't be anything
more than that.

01:13:19.899 --> 01:13:21.971
It's what I am
and what my family is.

01:13:22.106 --> 01:13:23.869
It's our way of life.

01:13:24.005 --> 01:13:27.103
I cannot throw all of that
away just for you.

01:13:28.575 --> 01:13:30.037
I don't understand.

01:13:30.173 --> 01:13:31.908
(BELL CLANGS)
And that alone

01:13:32.044 --> 01:13:33.945
is a reason
this could never work.

01:13:34.909 --> 01:13:36.083
It's over, Wade.

01:13:36.219 --> 01:13:37.487
(TRAIN HORN BLOWS)

01:13:40.115 --> 01:13:42.118
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING)

01:13:43.358 --> 01:13:44.494
(CRIES SOFTLY)

01:13:47.631 --> 01:13:50.027
(LAUGHING)
(UPBEAT FUSION MUSIC PLAYING)

01:13:57.966 --> 01:13:58.970
(BELL JINGLES)

01:14:07.074 --> 01:14:09.318
Everyone, welcome.

01:14:09.454 --> 01:14:11.816
It is good
to see your faces.

01:14:11.952 --> 01:14:14.623
I am honored
to have served you,

01:14:15.459 --> 01:14:17.318
but it's time
to move on.

01:14:18.226 --> 01:14:19.188
Come.

01:14:20.889 --> 01:14:22.256
My daughter,

01:14:22.392 --> 01:14:25.359
you are the Ember
of our family fire.

01:14:26.800 --> 01:14:28.702
That is why
I am so proud

01:14:28.838 --> 01:14:31.667
to have you take over
my life's work.

01:14:31.802 --> 01:14:33.807
(POPS, FIZZING)

01:14:37.510 --> 01:14:39.010
(CROWD EXCLAIMS)

01:14:40.076 --> 01:14:42.780
(APPLAUDING AND CHEERING)

01:14:42.915 --> 01:14:44.620
Pretty good
trick, huh?

01:14:45.921 --> 01:14:49.922
This is lantern I bring
from old country.

01:14:51.021 --> 01:14:53.689
Today, I pass it on to you.

01:14:53.825 --> 01:14:56.093
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

01:15:04.169 --> 01:15:05.542
WADE: I thought
of other reasons.

01:15:10.876 --> 01:15:12.838
Wade?
(CROWD GASPING)

01:15:12.974 --> 01:15:14.240
Oh, boy.

01:15:14.375 --> 01:15:15.581
What are you
doing here?

01:15:15.716 --> 01:15:16.947
You said
me not understanding

01:15:17.083 --> 01:15:18.586
is the reason
we can never work.

01:15:18.722 --> 01:15:20.220
But I thought
of other reasons.

01:15:20.355 --> 01:15:21.647
A bunch of 'em.

01:15:21.782 --> 01:15:24.524
Like, number one,
you're Fire,
I'm Water.

01:15:24.660 --> 01:15:26.393
I mean, come on,
that's crazy.

01:15:26.529 --> 01:15:27.757
Right?
(WOMAN ASSENTS)

01:15:27.893 --> 01:15:30.061
Who is this?
No idea.

01:15:30.197 --> 01:15:32.225
Number two,
I'm crashing
your party.

01:15:32.360 --> 01:15:33.864
Like, what kind
of a jerk am I?

01:15:33.999 --> 01:15:35.862
A pretty big one.
Right?

01:15:35.997 --> 01:15:36.967
Number three,

01:15:37.103 --> 01:15:40.207
I can't eat
your delicious foods.

01:15:40.342 --> 01:15:41.340
(SIZZLES, THUDS)

01:15:41.475 --> 01:15:42.875
(GURGLING)

01:15:43.011 --> 01:15:44.372
(VOICE STRAINS)
Ooh, very unpleasant.

01:15:44.507 --> 01:15:47.106
Wait, I know him.
He is food inspector.

01:15:47.241 --> 01:15:48.714
Oh, right.
Number four,

01:15:48.849 --> 01:15:51.216
I'm banned
from your father's shop.

01:15:51.352 --> 01:15:54.650
There are
a million reasons
why this can't work.

01:15:54.786 --> 01:15:56.115
A million nos.

01:15:56.251 --> 01:15:58.393
But there's also
one yes,

01:15:58.529 --> 01:16:00.421
we touched.
(ALL GASP)

01:16:00.556 --> 01:16:02.626
And when we did,
something happened to us,

01:16:02.761 --> 01:16:03.897
something impossible.

01:16:05.230 --> 01:16:07.334
We changed
each other's chemistry.

01:16:07.469 --> 01:16:08.737
BERNIE: Enough!

01:16:08.873 --> 01:16:10.771
What kind of
food inspection
is this?

01:16:10.906 --> 01:16:12.898
A food inspection
of the heart, sir.

01:16:13.034 --> 01:16:14.002
Who are you?

01:16:14.137 --> 01:16:15.337
Just a guy
who burst

01:16:15.473 --> 01:16:17.613
into your daughter's life
in a flooded old basement.

01:16:17.749 --> 01:16:19.844
So you are the one
who burst the pipes?

01:16:19.979 --> 01:16:21.442
What? Not me.
It was...

01:16:22.844 --> 01:16:24.148
You?

01:16:25.049 --> 01:16:26.550
You burst
the pipe?

01:16:26.685 --> 01:16:27.815
I...
Ember.

01:16:27.950 --> 01:16:29.389
Silence!
No!

01:16:29.524 --> 01:16:30.790
Take the chance.

01:16:30.926 --> 01:16:32.827
Let your father know
who you really are.

01:16:34.799 --> 01:16:37.632
Look, I had regrets
when my dad died.

01:16:37.767 --> 01:16:38.931
But because of you,
I learned

01:16:39.066 --> 01:16:42.063
to embrace the light
while it burns.

01:16:42.199 --> 01:16:43.806
(SPEAKING FIRISH) Tishok.

01:16:43.942 --> 01:16:47.509
You don't have forever
to say what you need to say.

01:16:47.644 --> 01:16:49.476
I love you,
Ember Lumen.

01:16:49.611 --> 01:16:51.604
(CROWD GASPS, MURMURS)

01:16:53.113 --> 01:16:55.179
And I'm pretty sure
you love me too.

01:16:58.685 --> 01:17:01.317
No, Wade, I don't.

01:17:01.951 --> 01:17:04.218
(CRACKING)

01:17:04.354 --> 01:17:06.826
That's not true.
I did their reading.

01:17:06.962 --> 01:17:09.230
(CROWD GASPS)
Bernie, it's love.

01:17:09.365 --> 01:17:10.896
It's true love.

01:17:11.032 --> 01:17:13.630
No, Mom, you're wrong.
Wade, go.

01:17:13.766 --> 01:17:14.698
But, Ember...

01:17:14.833 --> 01:17:16.530
I don't love you.

01:17:17.032 --> 01:17:18.536
(CRACKING)

01:17:18.671 --> 01:17:20.336
Go! (SOBS)

01:17:35.022 --> 01:17:37.118
You have been
seeing Water?

01:17:37.254 --> 01:17:38.393
(COUGHS)
Ashfa, I...

01:17:38.529 --> 01:17:40.323
You caused leak in shop?

01:17:41.595 --> 01:17:44.060
I trusted you.

01:17:44.195 --> 01:17:46.959
You will not
take over the shop.

01:17:47.094 --> 01:17:48.967
(COUGHING)

01:17:49.102 --> 01:17:51.339
I no longer retire.
(ALL GASP)

01:17:51.474 --> 01:17:53.408
(CROWD MURMURING)

01:17:53.544 --> 01:17:55.745
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING)

01:18:00.212 --> 01:18:02.444
(BROODING NEW-AGE
MUSIC PLAYS)

01:18:04.345 --> 01:18:06.349
(BIKE ENGINE ROARING)

01:18:15.393 --> 01:18:17.734
(BROODING NEW-AGE
MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:18:22.537 --> 01:18:23.905
(SIZZLING)

01:18:31.678 --> 01:18:32.881
(SIGHS)

01:18:40.055 --> 01:18:43.188
Why can't I just
be a good daughter?

01:18:44.328 --> 01:18:45.289
(SIGHS)

01:18:47.995 --> 01:18:49.964
(GRUNTS,
BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:18:57.265 --> 01:18:58.841
(DISTANT RUMBLING)

01:19:00.868 --> 01:19:03.241
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)
(CRACKS, SHATTERS)

01:19:19.220 --> 01:19:20.256
Firetown.

01:19:20.391 --> 01:19:22.260
(TIRES SCREECH)
(ENGINE ROARS)

01:19:23.495 --> 01:19:26.292
Well, one-way ticket
to anywhere but here.

01:19:26.427 --> 01:19:28.197
Go. Travel the world.

01:19:28.332 --> 01:19:30.299
Heal that
broken heart.

01:19:30.434 --> 01:19:33.504
My little drip,
drip baby boy.

01:19:33.640 --> 01:19:35.334
(CRYING)

01:19:35.470 --> 01:19:38.280
(SINGING)
♪♪ Drip, drip, drip
goes the baby boy ♪♪

01:19:38.415 --> 01:19:39.438
(BAWLING)

01:19:39.574 --> 01:19:41.243
I made you
a painting.

01:19:41.378 --> 01:19:43.512
(VOICE SHAKES)
It's of a lonely man

01:19:43.647 --> 01:19:45.320
(IN HIGH-PITCHED VOICE)
awash in sadness.

01:19:45.456 --> 01:19:47.450
(ALL BAWLING)

01:19:49.594 --> 01:19:51.589
(EMERGENCY SIREN WAILING)

01:19:51.724 --> 01:19:52.761
Ember.

01:19:52.897 --> 01:19:54.263
(THRILLING FUSION
MUSIC PLAYING)

01:19:54.398 --> 01:19:56.426
(ENGINE ROARING)

01:19:57.092 --> 01:19:58.098
(GASPS)

01:20:00.327 --> 01:20:02.030
EMBER: Mom, Dad!

01:20:02.165 --> 01:20:03.469
(ENGINE ROARING)

01:20:03.605 --> 01:20:04.698
(GASPS)

01:20:10.844 --> 01:20:12.644
(ENGINE ACCELERATES)

01:20:12.779 --> 01:20:14.706
(TIRES SCREECH)

01:20:14.842 --> 01:20:16.977
(THRILLING FUSION
MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:20:17.113 --> 01:20:18.085
(GRUNTS)

01:20:20.986 --> 01:20:22.184
Water's coming!

01:20:22.319 --> 01:20:24.326
(YELPING)
Watch out!

01:20:24.461 --> 01:20:26.223
Behind you!

01:20:26.359 --> 01:20:27.825
Climb! Climb!
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

01:20:27.960 --> 01:20:29.657
Flash flood!
Hurry!

01:20:30.258 --> 01:20:31.491
Mom, water!

01:20:31.626 --> 01:20:33.028
Get to higher ground!
(GASPS)

01:20:33.164 --> 01:20:34.629
Bernie!
Huh?

01:20:35.429 --> 01:20:36.396
(TIRES SCREECH)

01:20:36.532 --> 01:20:38.303
(SIZZLES)
(GRUNTS IN PAIN)

01:20:38.970 --> 01:20:40.175
(ENGINE REVS)

01:20:40.311 --> 01:20:41.306
(GRUNTS)

01:20:42.347 --> 01:20:43.341
(SHOUTS)

01:20:43.976 --> 01:20:45.805
(BOTH YELPING)

01:20:47.816 --> 01:20:49.516
(GRUNTS) The flame!

01:20:49.651 --> 01:20:50.648
Let me go!

01:20:50.784 --> 01:20:51.745
(GASPS)

01:20:52.180 --> 01:20:53.384
(GRUNTING)

01:20:54.215 --> 01:20:55.221
Ember, no!

01:20:57.285 --> 01:20:58.521
(VEHICLE CREAKS)

01:21:00.189 --> 01:21:01.689
(GRUNTING)

01:21:04.159 --> 01:21:05.132
(GASPS)

01:21:07.900 --> 01:21:09.268
(GRUNTING)

01:21:11.573 --> 01:21:12.937
(SIZZLES)

01:21:13.073 --> 01:21:14.871
(WADE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

01:21:15.007 --> 01:21:16.770
Wade?
Keyhole.

01:21:19.240 --> 01:21:20.807
(GRUNTS)

01:21:22.515 --> 01:21:24.479
I was hoping
to make a more
heroic entrance.

01:21:24.614 --> 01:21:27.218
You came back,
after everything I said.

01:21:27.354 --> 01:21:28.991
Are you kidding?
And miss all this?

01:21:30.120 --> 01:21:31.158
(GASPS)

01:21:32.456 --> 01:21:34.528
Hold the door.
(STRAINING)

01:21:34.663 --> 01:21:36.031
(GRUNTING)

01:21:44.435 --> 01:21:47.106
(GASPS)
(EMBER GRUNTS)

01:21:47.242 --> 01:21:49.635
No! No.
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no.

01:21:49.770 --> 01:21:51.376
(GLASS SHATTERS)
(GASPS)

01:21:51.944 --> 01:21:52.949
(GRUNTS)

01:21:55.709 --> 01:21:57.750
Ember,
we have to go!

01:21:57.885 --> 01:21:59.146
We have to go now!

01:21:59.282 --> 01:22:00.616
I can't leave.

01:22:00.752 --> 01:22:03.117
I'm sorry to say this,
but the shop is done.

01:22:03.253 --> 01:22:04.289
The flame is done.

01:22:04.424 --> 01:22:06.762
No! This is
my father's whole life.

01:22:06.897 --> 01:22:08.123
I'm not
going anywhere.

01:22:08.258 --> 01:22:09.660
(WINDOWS SHATTER)

01:22:09.796 --> 01:22:10.791
(GASPS)

01:22:11.798 --> 01:22:12.995
(GRUNTS)

01:22:13.130 --> 01:22:14.460
(GASPING)

01:22:14.595 --> 01:22:15.598
Throw me
that lantern.

01:22:18.140 --> 01:22:19.800
(GRUNTS)
(OBJECTS CLATTERING)

01:22:23.909 --> 01:22:24.871
(GRUNTS)

01:22:25.779 --> 01:22:26.873
No.

01:22:29.645 --> 01:22:31.119
No, no, no,
no, no, no.

01:22:32.856 --> 01:22:34.052
Oh, Wade.
(CHUCKLES)

01:22:34.187 --> 01:22:35.717
Thank you,
thank you.

01:22:37.254 --> 01:22:38.819
(SIZZLING)
Aah!

01:22:41.058 --> 01:22:42.031
(GRUNTS)

01:22:43.324 --> 01:22:44.825
(GRUNTING)

01:22:49.797 --> 01:22:51.799
(EMBER PANTING)
(BUBBLING)

01:22:57.077 --> 01:22:58.443
(PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYS)

01:22:59.641 --> 01:23:00.808
It's too hot
in here.

01:23:01.742 --> 01:23:03.176
(THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING)

01:23:03.311 --> 01:23:04.317
Climb!

01:23:09.055 --> 01:23:10.422
(WATER CRASHES)

01:23:13.062 --> 01:23:14.855
Back up! Back up!
(GRUNTS)

01:23:15.391 --> 01:23:16.894
(GRUNTS, GASPS)

01:23:17.029 --> 01:23:18.265
(BUBBLING)

01:23:24.173 --> 01:23:26.174
(GRUNTING)
(ROCKS CRUMBLING)

01:23:27.501 --> 01:23:28.471
(FIRE WHOOSHES)

01:23:28.607 --> 01:23:29.805
I have to open that up.
WADE: No!

01:23:29.940 --> 01:23:32.339
The water will come in
and you'll be snuffed out.

01:23:32.475 --> 01:23:33.846
But you're evaporating.

01:23:33.982 --> 01:23:35.582
I don't know what to do.

01:23:35.717 --> 01:23:36.684
It's okay.

01:23:36.819 --> 01:23:38.516
No, it's not okay!

01:23:39.714 --> 01:23:41.717
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:23:46.388 --> 01:23:47.363
(SIZZLES)

01:23:47.498 --> 01:23:48.762
Ember,

01:23:48.897 --> 01:23:50.391
I have no regrets.

01:23:50.526 --> 01:23:51.528
You gave me something

01:23:51.663 --> 01:23:53.364
people search for
their whole lives.

01:23:53.500 --> 01:23:56.829
But I can't exist
in a world without you.

01:23:56.965 --> 01:23:59.999
(SOBS) I'm sorry
I didn't say it before.

01:24:00.501 --> 01:24:01.434
(SNIFFLES)

01:24:01.569 --> 01:24:03.039
I love you, Wade.

01:24:03.174 --> 01:24:05.180
(BUBBLING)

01:24:06.742 --> 01:24:08.909
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:24:10.684 --> 01:24:13.782
I really do love it
when your light does that.

01:24:16.517 --> 01:24:17.819
(SIZZLING)

01:24:27.761 --> 01:24:28.768
(SOLEMN MUSIC PLAYING)

01:24:28.903 --> 01:24:29.996
(GRUNTING)

01:24:31.374 --> 01:24:32.507
WOMAN: They're in the hearth!
(GASPS)

01:24:32.643 --> 01:24:34.000
(GRUNTS)

01:24:38.475 --> 01:24:40.644
(SOLEMN MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:24:41.576 --> 01:24:42.778
Wade is gone.

01:24:43.720 --> 01:24:45.220
Oh, my daughter.

01:24:46.252 --> 01:24:47.750
He saved me. (SIGHS)

01:25:01.770 --> 01:25:02.897
Dad...

01:25:04.240 --> 01:25:07.399
this is all
my fault. (CRIES)

01:25:07.535 --> 01:25:08.837
The shop...

01:25:10.878 --> 01:25:11.977
Wade.

01:25:12.112 --> 01:25:14.183
(CONTINUES CRYING)

01:25:16.010 --> 01:25:18.385
I need to tell you
the truth.

01:25:19.286 --> 01:25:21.355
I don't want
to run the shop.

01:25:22.586 --> 01:25:24.660
I know that was your dream,

01:25:24.795 --> 01:25:26.327
but it's not mine.

01:25:27.356 --> 01:25:28.956
I'm sorry.

01:25:30.131 --> 01:25:31.827
I'm a bad daughter.

01:25:34.301 --> 01:25:36.304
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:25:41.535 --> 01:25:42.977
Ember,

01:25:43.112 --> 01:25:45.604
the shop was never
the dream.

01:25:45.740 --> 01:25:48.049
You were the dream.

01:25:48.184 --> 01:25:50.648
You were always
the dream.

01:25:53.086 --> 01:25:55.048
(CRYING)

01:25:58.521 --> 01:26:00.394
I loved him, Dad.

01:26:01.129 --> 01:26:03.122
(EMBER CONTINUES CRYING)

01:26:10.941 --> 01:26:12.868
(WADE CRIES DISTANTLY)

01:26:25.546 --> 01:26:26.717
(CLUNKS)

01:26:32.257 --> 01:26:33.691
Butterfly.

01:26:36.359 --> 01:26:40.533
Butterfly.
Windshield wipers.
Half a butterfly.

01:26:41.938 --> 01:26:43.932
(WADE CRYING)

01:26:44.940 --> 01:26:45.934
(CLUNKING)

01:26:48.045 --> 01:26:49.673
An old man
on his deathbed

01:26:49.808 --> 01:26:52.175
remembers the summer
he fell in love.

01:26:52.311 --> 01:26:54.283
(WADE SOBBING)

01:26:58.649 --> 01:27:00.516
She was out of his league

01:27:00.651 --> 01:27:02.185
and he was young
and scared.

01:27:02.320 --> 01:27:03.453
(CHUCKLES)

01:27:03.589 --> 01:27:05.423
He let her go,
thinking surely

01:27:05.558 --> 01:27:06.955
summer would
come again.

01:27:07.524 --> 01:27:08.697
It never did.

01:27:08.833 --> 01:27:11.300
(WADE CRYING)

01:27:13.028 --> 01:27:15.727
You are perfect match.
Ten out of ten.

01:27:15.863 --> 01:27:17.229
(CRYING INTENSIFIES)

01:27:18.606 --> 01:27:20.333
I don't understand.
What's going on?

01:27:20.469 --> 01:27:23.140
Just say something
to make Water guy
cry, okay?

01:27:23.275 --> 01:27:25.441
Um... Uh...

01:27:25.577 --> 01:27:27.415
You are no
longer panned.

01:27:28.118 --> 01:27:30.083
WADE: Banned.
Banned.

01:27:30.218 --> 01:27:32.179
(WADE CRIES INTENSELY)

01:27:32.315 --> 01:27:35.653
I want to explore the world
with you, Wade Ripple.

01:27:35.789 --> 01:27:38.285
I want to have you
with me in my life.

01:27:38.421 --> 01:27:39.421
Forever.

01:27:39.557 --> 01:27:41.990
(HOPEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:27:44.131 --> 01:27:45.532
(BUBBLING)

01:27:51.941 --> 01:27:54.407
WADE: Whoa!

01:27:54.543 --> 01:27:57.405
Your, uh, chimney
needs cleaning.

01:27:57.540 --> 01:27:58.846
(GASPING)

01:27:58.981 --> 01:27:59.946
(SIZZLES)

01:28:00.081 --> 01:28:01.075
(CHUCKLES)

01:28:04.817 --> 01:28:07.180
(PEACEFUL NEW-AGE
MUSIC PLAYING)

01:28:20.371 --> 01:28:24.003
I knew it.
My nose always knows.

01:28:24.139 --> 01:28:26.232
(ALL LAUGHING)

01:28:34.183 --> 01:28:35.384
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:28:36.480 --> 01:28:37.815
(SLOSHING)

01:28:37.950 --> 01:28:41.319
If you were a vegetable,
you'd be a cute-cumber.

01:28:41.455 --> 01:28:42.386
(GRUNTS)
(FLOWER PINGS)

01:28:42.522 --> 01:28:44.023
(GASPS)
My queen.

01:28:44.158 --> 01:28:45.551
(GIGGLES)

01:28:45.687 --> 01:28:48.660
Ah! I can't believe
I was gonna shut
this place down.

01:28:48.795 --> 01:28:50.694
(CHUCKLES) Whoa. Sorry.
(OBJECTS RATTLE)

01:28:50.830 --> 01:28:54.461
(GASPS) Fern,
you're a Windbreakers fan?

01:28:54.596 --> 01:28:56.004
Toot toot.

01:28:56.140 --> 01:28:58.205
(IN FLIRTY TONE) Toot toot.

01:28:58.340 --> 01:28:59.700
Oy, you know
what I like best

01:28:59.836 --> 01:29:01.176
about running
this shop?

01:29:01.312 --> 01:29:03.702
Not having to eat
Bernie's kol-nuts?

01:29:03.838 --> 01:29:04.877
(ALL LAUGHING)

01:29:05.013 --> 01:29:06.006
Sorry,

01:29:06.142 --> 01:29:08.883
I couldn't hear you
through my retirement.

01:29:09.019 --> 01:29:11.013
(ALL LAUGHING)

01:29:18.952 --> 01:29:20.220
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

01:29:21.328 --> 01:29:22.596
(BELL JINGLES)

01:29:23.828 --> 01:29:25.797
Ooh!
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

01:29:27.861 --> 01:29:28.903
(BLOWING)

01:29:29.038 --> 01:29:29.962
(BELL JINGLES)

01:29:30.097 --> 01:29:32.100
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:29:34.706 --> 01:29:36.377
(BELL JINGLES)
Hey!

01:29:36.513 --> 01:29:37.978
Hi, Wade.
Hey, Wade! Yo, yo, yo!

01:29:38.113 --> 01:29:39.277
(WADE CHUCKLES)

01:29:39.412 --> 01:29:41.582
Ember, it's time.

01:29:43.177 --> 01:29:45.586
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:29:46.752 --> 01:29:48.748
You know, I...
I'm not really one

01:29:48.883 --> 01:29:49.957
for tearful goodbyes.

01:29:50.092 --> 01:29:52.125
(SOBS) Oh, Wade.

01:29:52.261 --> 01:29:55.189
You big liar. (SOBS)

01:29:55.324 --> 01:29:57.389
(SINGING)
♪♪ Drip, drip, drip

01:29:57.524 --> 01:29:59.758
BOTH:
♪♪ Goes the baby boy♪♪

01:29:59.894 --> 01:30:01.932
(BOTH BAWLING)

01:30:03.705 --> 01:30:06.567
Uh, are you sure
about this one?

01:30:06.702 --> 01:30:07.773
I'm sure.

01:30:08.505 --> 01:30:09.743
Dad,

01:30:09.878 --> 01:30:12.780
I'm sorry
the internship
is so far away.

01:30:12.915 --> 01:30:14.979
I mean,
it's the best glass design
company in the world,

01:30:15.115 --> 01:30:16.812
but who knows
if it'll become
a real job.

01:30:16.948 --> 01:30:18.111
I'll be back
in a few months anyway,

01:30:18.247 --> 01:30:19.881
and it might not
end up being anything...

01:30:20.016 --> 01:30:22.324
Ay-yah. Shh.
Go, start new life.

01:30:22.460 --> 01:30:24.459
Your mother and I
will be here.

01:30:24.594 --> 01:30:26.921
Now, with more time
for hanky-panky.

01:30:27.056 --> 01:30:28.325
(SPEAKING FIRISH) E shutsh!

01:30:28.461 --> 01:30:30.466
(ALL LAUGHING)

01:30:31.233 --> 01:30:32.358
(SHIP HORN HONKS)

01:30:35.965 --> 01:30:38.199
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:30:56.290 --> 01:30:57.658
(CINDER GASPS)

01:31:17.271 --> 01:31:19.614
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:31:28.224 --> 01:31:30.053
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

01:31:38.997 --> 01:31:41.662
(STEAL THE SHOW
BY LAUV PLAYING)

01:31:41.797 --> 01:31:43.605
(VOCALIZING)

01:31:49.472 --> 01:31:52.044
♪♪ Started out
on a one-way train

01:31:52.180 --> 01:31:54.672
♪♪ Always knew where
I was gonna go next

01:31:54.808 --> 01:31:57.246
♪♪ Didn't know
until I saw your face

01:31:57.382 --> 01:31:59.854
♪♪ I was missing out
on every moment

01:31:59.989 --> 01:32:02.416
♪♪ You'll be one and
baby, I'll be two

01:32:02.552 --> 01:32:05.253
♪♪ Would you mind it
if I said I'm into you?

01:32:06.527 --> 01:32:07.926
♪♪ I'm into you

01:32:09.223 --> 01:32:12.192
♪♪ So if it's real

01:32:12.328 --> 01:32:15.531
♪♪ Then, darlin', let me know

01:32:15.666 --> 01:32:17.672
(VOCALIZING)

01:32:19.574 --> 01:32:22.839
♪♪ I wouldn't mind

01:32:22.974 --> 01:32:25.871
♪♪ If you steal the show

01:32:26.006 --> 01:32:28.309
(VOCALIZING)

01:32:46.637 --> 01:32:49.101
♪♪ You and I
we go together

01:32:49.236 --> 01:32:51.599
♪♪ You're the sky
I'll be the weather

01:32:51.735 --> 01:32:54.633
♪♪ A pretty thing, the sun
and rain, who knew?

01:32:55.302 --> 01:32:56.844
♪♪ Oh-oh-oh, yeah

01:32:56.979 --> 01:32:59.574
♪♪ Summer night
perfect occasion

01:32:59.710 --> 01:33:03.047
♪♪ Where am I?
You know
I'll be waitin' for you

01:33:04.519 --> 01:33:06.211
♪♪ Oh, for you

01:33:06.346 --> 01:33:09.282
♪♪ So if it's real

01:33:09.418 --> 01:33:12.720
♪♪ Then, darlin', let me know

01:33:12.855 --> 01:33:14.828
(VOCALIZING)

01:33:16.763 --> 01:33:19.962
♪♪ I wouldn't mind

01:33:20.097 --> 01:33:22.961
♪♪ If you steal the show

01:33:23.096 --> 01:33:24.904
(VOCALIZING)

01:33:26.938 --> 01:33:29.775
♪♪ So if it's real

01:33:29.911 --> 01:33:33.180
♪♪ Then, darlin', let me know

01:33:33.315 --> 01:33:35.310
(VOCALIZING)

01:33:37.619 --> 01:33:40.455
♪♪ I wouldn't mind

01:33:40.590 --> 01:33:43.181
♪♪ If you steal the show

